column31: Ok, I am going to write this because I am sick and tired of Kate Brown lying about what is going on and the local news media being complicit in her lies. Here are the **facts** based on actual data from OHA. As of today there have been 234,769 persons tested for Covid-19. 226,348 tested negative. That means that 8485 persons, or 3.6% of those tested were positive or presumptive positive. We have had 204 deaths attributed to Covid-19. That equates to .0004% of the population of Oregon. Here is where Kate’s panic attack over recent cases falls apart. Up until March 31, 2020 there were 12,883 person tested, 606 of which had tested positive. The percentage of those tested that had positive results were **4.7%.** During April of 2020 there were 41,589 persons tested, 1,756 of which had tested positive. The percentage of those tested that had positive results were **4.2%** During May of 2020 there were 73,061 persons tested, 1,733 of which had tested positive. The percentage of those tested that had positive results were **2.4%** During June of 2020 there were 103,261 persons tested, 4,183 of which had tested positive. The percentage of those tested that had positive results were **4%.** As you can see, the numbers of positive cases have gone up directly proportionally with the number of those tested. There is no massive influx of new cases, there are simply more people being tested! The death rate, month by month is as follows, (again, data direct from OHA) Up to March 31 - 16 deaths in Oregon During April - 83 deaths in Oregon During May - 50 deaths in Oregon During June - 50 deaths in Oregon Kate Brown has been lying to us about what is going on in order to extend her tyrannical control of our state. If this does not convince us to recall her, I think nothing will. RECALL KATE BROWN!
Here it comes! I believe the only way to stop this is not letter writing, not emails, but we the people standing up in mass and saying NO MORE! What say you?

column31: Some information that should be shared! My husband is a cancer patient. As a result of chemo and radiation he has pneumonia. He needed to be admitted to the hospital for IV antibiotics and oxygen. He was seen @ Miami Valley Hospital in Dayton. Without us being told AT ANY POINT... he was being admitted to a Covid Unit. He was being admitted to a Covid unit... He tested negative for Covid TWICE. While being taken to his room I was stopped by a nurse that told me it was an isolated floor and I could not be there! We were NEVER TOLD until I pressed to know WHY!!! I refused to leave and refused to let my husband stay! We were told he NEEDED medical treatment in a hospital setting or risk death! The doctor plainly said to me “he could die”... my response was “that’s fine BUT it won’t be HERE!!” He does NOT have Covid and has not been exposed to Covid, he tested negative (as precaution TWICE) he is a cancer patient with a condition directly related to radiation treatment!!! I said we would wait the 12 hours for his Covid test to come back negative AGAIN and return. We were advised that he would be tested for Covid again and placed in a Covid unit REGARDLESS of the result!!!! His family doctor told us that it would be certain death for him to be exposed to Covid! I’m left with no other option than to treat my husband with basic medicine, hope and a prayer!!!! There are NO WORDS to describe the fury that I feel over this situation! It’s incredibly sad that in the year 2020 in the United States a CANCER patient cannot get the treatment they need and deserve without being subjected to unnecessary risk. A regular ICU STILL exists! There’s no way in hell I was going to leave him and ALLOW him to be counted as a Covid death!

The Justice Centre has released a comprehensive Charter analysis of the violations of Ontarians’ freedoms to move, travel, assemble, associate and worship, as protected by the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms. Entitled “Unprecedented and Unjustified,” this Charter analysis of Ontario’s response to COVID-19 addresses: the nature of the government’s lockdown measures and how they violate Charter freedoms; the Charter’s requirement of government to justify these violations; the inaccurate claims made about COVID-19 in March and April of 2020; the economic harm caused by lockdown measures; the relationship between a prosperous economy and the ability to pay for good health care; the negative impact of the lockdown measures on health care; and a detailed analysis of the Command Table’s April 3 COVID-19 modelling and April 20 COVID-19 modelling. Unprecedented and Unjustified questions whether the Ontario Government has properly considered COVID-19 within its global and historical context. The 1957-58 “Asian flu” and the 1968-69 “Hong Kong flu” each claimed one million lives around the world, when the world population was less than half of what it is today. In more average years, the flu sadly takes between 291,000 and 646,000 lives, most of them vulnerable elderly people who are already sick with one or more serious health conditions. Likewise, the primary impact of COVID-19 has been on residents in long-term care homes – approximately 75% of all deaths have occurred in these homes, the population of which represents approximately half a percent of all Ontarians. As of June 22, 2020, COVID-19 had apparently killed 473,000 people around the world, although this number includes people who died of other causes while also having this virus. While very tragic, the number of deaths with COVID-19 is within the range of the annual flu and, like the flu, primarily impacts the elderly and vulnerable. Yet the Ontario Government’s lockdown measures are based on the now disproven notion that COVID-19 is an unusually deadly killer that everyone should be alarmed by and that is a dire threat to all segments of the population. “The concern that COVID-19 is going to result in hundreds of thousands of deaths was already disproven many weeks ago, so why is the lockdown still in place?” asks lawyer John Carpay, President of the Justice Centre. “The Charter serves to protect Canada as a “free and democratic society” where governments respect the fundamental freedoms of Canadians to move, travel, assemble, associate and worship. The onus is on politicians in Ontario – not the citizens who elected them – to justify violations of these fundamental freedoms.” “The Ontario Government’s lockdown measures obviously violate the Charter freedoms of Ontarians to move, travel, assemble, associate, and worship. The daily routines of millions of Ontarians, and their ability to earn a living to support themselves and their loved ones, have been dramatically impacted since large segments of the public and business spheres were ordered to close,” adds Justice Centre staff lawyer Lisa Bildy. “Tens of thousands of Ontarians were affected when hospitals were reserved primarily for COVID-19 patients, and many of these individuals are still suffering on long wait lists today. It will be months or even years before we know the full death toll of the decision to cancel and postpone tens of thousand of medically necessary surgeries, after counting all the cardiac patients who died while waiting for heart surgery, and after counting additional cancer deaths caused by lack of timely diagnosis and treatment. Meanwhile, hospitals have not been operating at anything approaching full capacity, even when the curve was already flat,” continues Bildy.

NO MASK INFO: Hi Everyone, here’s some helpful info on this topic... The Executive Orders for masks apply ONLY for people who can medically tolerate a mask. (Please read them yourselves - they’re public on your local gov sites). If a business owner chooses to create a policy that requires a mask, they must be reminded that their policy MUST be ADA compliant - meaning they cannot discriminate against someone that can’t medically tolerate a face covering. Establishments are now being sued in federal court (where state and local has no jurisdiction). This is because their policy cannot override existing law. Their policy must be within the law and be compliant. Not only do they risk ADA violation, they also risk OSHA violation since the case law has set precedent that this (mask) product carries inherent risk of injury or death to a person who wears it. Additionally, they risk being sued for millions by anyone who has been hurt on premises just like the 6 people who are now suing after being forced to wear a mask to enter a store and passed out and cracked their head open on premises. Some of these plaintiffs didn’t even realize that they couldn’t medically tolerate a face covering! Let’s protect business owners by educating them to read the Order carefully and understand that it DOESN’T apply to everyone. That business owners/managers are not Primary Physicians and cannot determine someone’s medical predisposition and force them to put a product on their body that carries inherent risk of injury or death (according to case law). They must also be careful to avoid HIPPA violations and NOT ask anyone about their medical history or predisposition. They sometimes make the mistake of asking why someone’s medically exempt or for a doctor’s note - Ouch! Big “No no”. Business owners and employees are also not attorneys and don’t realize the risk of liability they’re exposing themselves to by forcing someone to wear a mask. And finally, they can’t discriminate and treat someone that can’t breathe or has a medical condition, differently or serviced out on the street as everyone else is happily serviced inside. It’s purely discriminatory which again exposes the owner to potential damages. This is why major corporate chains are now taking their signs down or revising them to say “masks suggested or keep a six foot distance”. Big Corporate Establishments get advised by high paying lawyers about the potential risk of forcing customers to wear a face covering. Small biz owners may not afford the same kind of legal guidance. The lawsuits are pouring in by the day. And for tens of millions of dollars in damages per lawsuit. Requiring someone to wear a mask carries major risk to the business owner and customer. Let’s support small businesses by giving them the info they need to pass onto their corporate litigators for advice so that they can keep their doors open and businesses safe by not forcing their loyal patrons to harm themselves! (This Post isn’t meant to be legal advice-you can simply have Docs reviewed by an establishment’s corporate counsel which so far has resulted in store policy revision every time).

The Right Honourable Justin Trudeau Prime Minister of Canada Office of the Prime Minister 80 Wellington Street Ottawa, ON K1A 0A2 Dear Mr. Trudeau, I am soon to be a fourth year Journalism and Humanities student at Carleton University. During a mid-evening reporting class in March, I recall our Carleton newsroom bursting with cries of a pandemic that would soon change the world. Initially, alongside my peers, friends, and family I was more than concerned for the welfare of my compatriots. I am worried for my fellow Canadians more tonight as I pen this letter to you than I was that fateful evening during my reporting class. As you know, according to the CDC SarsCov2 has an Infection Fatality Rate of .26% and possibly lower as up to 80% of cases are mild or asymptomatic. This single fact alone begs to end the lockdown. The Humanities program is a reflection of my personal interest in history. I especially take to the history of World War 2. Recall, the actions the German occupying forces initially took before horrifically and unimaginably inflicting genocide on the innocent Polish Jews. They were broken up into a clear dichotomy, “Essential” and “Non-essential” workers. This alone began the torture of those innocents Poles. This illogical classification single-handedly broke apart their developed society. It compelled me to make this comparison to your lockdown. I’ve personally witnessed what this supposedly helpful determination has done to both “essential” and “non-essential” workers in Ontario. Nearly a third of businesses have been forced to close. I look around my once vibrant neighbourhood and I can only take note of numerous ‘for sale’ signs. Why have you chosen to financially destroy the Canadian people based upon ludicrous designations like “non-essential” and “essential work”? Mr. Trudeau, the leader of a country should know, all work is essential. To think otherwise is absolutely absurd and is only reminiscent of fascism. Save our country, and end the lockdown and all associated stifling “new normal” measures. Your fellow Canadian, Zak G.M. cc. Late last night, approaching midnight, The Age published an article by an Australian politician expressing his opinion that people who choose to abstain from a Covid-19 vaccination should be prejudiced against.

It is the opinion of Raff Ciccone, federal Labor senator for Victoria, that harsh restrictions on where the unvaccinated may work and socialise should be put in place.

In the articled titled “New COVID-19 restrictions will be needed for anti-vaxxers’ Ciccone likens the pandemic to a ‘real-life Hollywood blockbuster’ and describes the right to choose being employed by free citizens as a ‘diabolical plot twist’.

Ciccone suggests ‘we’ (The government? The media?) should prepare for this ‘diabolical’ expression of free will by building on the program of tracking childhood vaccination with the Australian Immunisation Register and expanding it to include all Australians; men, women AND children.

And Ciccone, this so-called representative of the people, is not interested in democratic discussion saying he has “no interest in your alternative "facts" or your conspiracy theories” and claims that those against a vaccine for all are in the minority. On this point he is definitely wrong. column35: Pendleton Round-Up
column36:
We are devastated to share this news with you. "Let'er Buck" & “On with the show” is in our DNA, and for only the third time in our history our September event will not take place. The decision to not host the world famous Pendleton Round-Up and Happy Canyon 2020 event was a really tough one, but a necessary one. We are comforted knowing our community is not being put in harm's way with the novel coronavirus, for that would be a burden we could not bear.

For 110 years the Pendleton Round-Up and for 104 years the Happy Canyon have been a celebration of community and a catalyst to support education, local not for profits, service organizations, and provide a direct benefit to the regional economy.

A donation fund coined LET’ER BUCK CARES was established to support and benefit the various community organizations. These organizations have relied on the week of Round-Up and Happy Canyon as their main source of income to support their causes and further their missions of support to the community. The Pendleton Round-Up and the Happy Canyon will invest in the fund to create and establish the fund for the community benefit to assist with the impacts of not having the 2020 traditional events.

The LET’ER BUCK CARES fund will allow all 2020 ticket holders and supporters the opportunity to provide assistance to these organizations during the upcoming year. Through the LET’ER BUCK CARES fund, ticket holders will have four options for their purchased 2020 tickets.

• Option 1: Designate that the refund of purchased tickets will go to the LET’ER BUCK CARES fund.
• Option 2: Provide a combination of refund and designation of some of those funds to LET’ER BUCK CARES fund.
• Option 3: Roll purchased tickets to our 2021 event.
• Option 4: Receive a refund for purchased tickets.

Through our Pendleton Round-Up website (https://www.pendletonroundup.com/p/tickets/leter-buck-cares-fund) you will also have the ability for those who might not have purchased tickets, but who would like to be part of this effort to donate to the LET’ER BUCK CARES fund. Full refund donations to the fund, will be tax deductible through the Oregon Community Foundation, will come back to support the local civic, non-profit, youth organizations, contract personnel and others that are instrumental during the week of the Pendleton Round-Up and Happy Canyon. 

These groups rely on fundraising efforts at the Pendleton Round-Up and Happy Canyon in order to operate their programs benefiting our community and region. We are also working with the Pendleton Chamber of Commerce to provide some stimulus funds through this program to benefit community businesses that will feel an impact to their operations caused by the lack of visitors to Pendleton this year. 

So far in 2020 we have endured many tragedies, which reminds us what was penned about the Pendleton Round-Up in 1911:  “When things do not go right for you, when circumstances seem to be against you and fate deals you a blow between the eyes, remember, what the cowboys say in the great Northwest.  Just grit your teeth, get another hold…and Let’er Buck! 

Through the support of this fund, the community will be able to support the organizations that are an integral part of the success of the Pendleton Round-Up and Happy Canyon. 

Let’er Buck and On With The Show!

DONATIONS & TICKET REFUNDS:
https://www.pendletonroundup.com/p/tickets/leter-buck-cares-fund

SOME LIGHT READING FOR THE FOLKS HERE... Everyday is No Mask day for me. I went to a gas station in Portland today to have some propane tanks filled. I was told by the clerk that I have to wear a mask or I can't come in the store. I showed her my lanyard and said I have a medical exemption. She told me to leave the store immediately. To my surprise, another customer inside said, "you can't discriminate against him if he has a medical condition." I stepped outside the door onto the sidewalk and asked her if someone could come outside and fill my tanks. She told me again to leave. I asked her to call the manager so I can talk with him. Another clerk in the store said I could come back in and pay for the propane and he'd meet me outside. I went outside, he filled the tanks and then the manager showed up and started harassing me about not wearing a mask. I asked him to call the police, and if he didn't do it, I would do it to save him the trouble. He called the Portland PD. Two officers showed up and were very professional and courteous. I offered them my DL for identification and they asked me for my side of the story. I told them my story, thanked them for their service in these dangerous times, and asked them to have a talk to the manager to see if he had a written plan and offered training to his employees on the proper fitting and use of OSHA approved N95 particulate respirators for their safety. column31: Bill Gates says 'Final Hurdle' To Distributing a Covid-19 Vaccine Will be Convincing People to TAKE IT June 26, 2020 Microsoft billionaire Bill Gates lamented the US is 'not even close' to doing enough to fight the pandemic, before warning that the vaccine he wants to inject into every human on the planet does require their consent first. Speaking to Anderson Cooper at a CNN town hall on Thursday, Gates insisted the US was “experiencing a rebound” in Covid-19 infections even accounting for the increase in testing. That increase, the software tycoon reminded his interviewers, was accomplished by local governments in spite of - not because of - the White House. Gates seemed miffed that Washington wasn’t following his instructions more closely, complaining that “it’s possible to ramp up testing for a new pathogen very, very fast” if they’d just do as they were told. He blamed the higher infection numbers in the US, which continues to lead the world with upwards of 2.5 million confirmed cases and over 125,000 deaths, on the nation’s failure to adopt the same measures as everyone else. “Other countries” are “restraining their behavior,” imposing restrictive lockdowns and quarantines, and adopting comprehensive contact tracing, Gates hinted, sounding impatient with the US’ “very large case spread,” which he called “embarrassing.” Some people almost feel like [Covid-19 is] a political thing, which is unfortunate. “Even to inconvenience themselves with masks requires maybe someone they know to not only test positive but maybe get very sick as well,” he added. Gates, who has repeatedly expressed a desire to inoculate the world’s population with whatever vaccine emerges from the research laboratories he is funding, admitted the shot might be rolled out before it’s working perfectly. “It’s possible the vaccine will be better at protecting you individually and not stop you from transmitting…it’s not guaranteed that the vaccine will be a perfect transmission blocker.” Boasting that “the logistics in the US are not an issue at all,” Gates bragged that “we can get this thing out there” before acknowledging that “you’ll have a ‘choice’ whether you take the vaccine or not, so there’s that final hurdle.” The billionaire seemed unconcerned by the “vaccine hesitancy” factor, however, even though over a third of Americans have professed some concern over the safety of a coronavirus vaccine, citing the politicization of the issue, the rushed timetable, the less-than-stellar reputation of some of the individuals involved, and other issues. Some 70 to 80 percent of the world’s population will have to take the vaccine before anyone can hope to live a normal life again “with people taking vacations,” travel, and sporting events, Gates explained, implying they had no choice.

column31: My Dear Friends, please share this letter widely, on social media (outside FB as well), media outlets, MPPs, MPs etc. This is a very important matter that will affect all of us at some point. RE: Access to Patient Mr. Suhar Valdman, Welland Hospital 65 Third St. Welland ON L3B 4W6 To Whom It May Concern, June 22,2020 Mr. Suhar Valdman is currently a patient in your hospital. His wife, Mrs. Valdman was given a paltry 30 min window to spend with her beloved husband today. She requested more time to feed him lunch and was denied. Mr. Valdman’s only daughter Silvia, was informed by hospital staff that she will not be allowed to see her father unless he is on his death bed. Silvia and I represent a large group of activists in Canada. We are horrified by the draconian policy of this hospital and many other hospitals in Ontario under the pretext of patient safety. This is especially perplexing given the memorandum issued on June 15 by Dr. David Williams (Chief Medical Officer of Health). Dr. Williams recommended that all public and private hospitals allow visitations from family and caregivers. According to Dr. Williams, “Visits from family and caregivers and other visitors contribute greatly to a patient’s quality of life and well-being.” Let’s examine the data. According to the CDC, the infection fatality rate from COVID-19 is 0.26% and likely lower as up to 80% of cases are mild or asymptomatic. According to the WHO there is no evidence of asymptomatic transmission of the SarsCov2 virus. There is a well documented study to support this as well as other anecdotal studies. 63% of deaths in Ontario occurred in Long Term Care Facilities (LTCFs). It is important to heed these deaths in Ontario’s LTCF and elucidate their causes. On May 20, Brigadier General Commander C.J.J. Mialkowski submitted a gruesome report on five of Ontario’s LTCFs. The details are overt in proving that neglect and abuse of the residents was rampant. Here are some of the disturbing details: -verbal abuse and aggressive behaviour by caretakers -significant gross fecal contamination -insect infestation -delayed changing of soiled residents -forceful feeding and hydration causing audible chocking /aspiration -patients crying for help with staff not responding until after 30 min to 2 hours -residents not bathed for several weeks Would these conditions have festered if these vulnerable residents were allowed to have visitation from family members? In addition, the report states the following: “NO psychosocial support for these residents who have all of a sudden had their families taken away, anxiety and depression being treated with narcotics and benzodiazepenes to sedate them.” Residents reported to have felt, “Scared and feel alone like they’re in jail.” Despite wide-spread knowledge of this report Welland Hospital is refusing Mr. Valdman the love and care of his wife and daughter during the most vulnerable time in his life. Mr. Valdman survived the Nazi occupation in Romania. Now, nearing the end of his life he is the victim of medical tyranny. The extreme stress and anxiety of his immediate family is a consequence of his unjust treatment. Furthermore, in the complex matter of advocating for a patient’s rights, and treatment decisions, it is very difficult to do so remotely, family members need to be able to assess the patient in person and discuss matters with care providers in person. We have read the accounts of many people whose loved ones died in isolation deprived of love, care and compassion. Is this not a crime against humanity? How many people in Ontario hospitals and LTCFs have died alone? We demand the immediate access to Mr. Valdman by his beloved wife and daughter. They are both willing to wear PPE at the standard of other workers in the hospital who have access to patients. We look forward to a quick resolution of this matter. Sincerely, Dr. Jasmine Gilani and Silvia Valdman, LL.B. Silvia Valdman’s cell: 289-241-1000

column31: The Justice Centre has released a comprehensive Charter analysis of the violations of Ontarians’ freedoms to move, travel, assemble, associate and worship, as protected by the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms. Entitled “Unprecedented and Unjustified,” this Charter analysis of Ontario’s response to COVID-19 addresses: the nature of the government’s lockdown measures and how they violate Charter freedoms; the Charter’s requirement of government to justify these violations; the inaccurate claims made about COVID-19 in March and April of 2020; the economic harm caused by lockdown measures; the relationship between a prosperous economy and the ability to pay for good health care; the negative impact of the lockdown measures on health care; and a detailed analysis of the Command Table’s April 3 COVID-19 modelling and April 20 COVID-19 modelling. Unprecedented and Unjustified questions whether the Ontario Government has properly considered COVID-19 within its global and historical context. The 1957-58 “Asian flu” and the 1968-69 “Hong Kong flu” each claimed one million lives around the world, when the world population was less than half of what it is today. In more average years, the flu sadly takes between 291,000 and 646,000 lives, most of them vulnerable elderly people who are already sick with one or more serious health conditions. Likewise, the primary impact of COVID-19 has been on residents in long-term care homes – approximately 75% of all deaths have occurred in these homes, the population of which represents approximately half a percent of all Ontarians. As of June 22, 2020, COVID-19 had apparently killed 473,000 people around the world, although this number includes people who died of other causes while also having this virus. While very tragic, the number of deaths with COVID-19 is within the range of the annual flu and, like the flu, primarily impacts the elderly and vulnerable. Yet the Ontario Government’s lockdown measures are based on the now disproven notion that COVID-19 is an unusually deadly killer that everyone should be alarmed by and that is a dire threat to all segments of the population. “The concern that COVID-19 is going to result in hundreds of thousands of deaths was already disproven many weeks ago, so why is the lockdown still in place?” asks lawyer John Carpay, President of the Justice Centre. “The Charter serves to protect Canada as a “free and democratic society” where governments respect the fundamental freedoms of Canadians to move, travel, assemble, associate and worship. The onus is on politicians in Ontario – not the citizens who elected them – to justify violations of these fundamental freedoms.” “The Ontario Government’s lockdown measures obviously violate the Charter freedoms of Ontarians to move, travel, assemble, associate, and worship. The daily routines of millions of Ontarians, and their ability to earn a living to support themselves and their loved ones, have been dramatically impacted since large segments of the public and business spheres were ordered to close,” adds Justice Centre staff lawyer Lisa Bildy. “Tens of thousands of Ontarians were affected when hospitals were reserved primarily for COVID-19 patients, and many of these individuals are still suffering on long wait lists today. It will be months or even years before we know the full death toll of the decision to cancel and postpone tens of thousand of medically necessary surgeries, after counting all the cardiac patients who died while waiting for heart surgery, and after counting additional cancer deaths caused by lack of timely diagnosis and treatment. Meanwhile, hospitals have not been operating at anything approaching full capacity, even when the curve was already flat,” continues Bildy.

column31: From a Retired Navy Doctor.. As a preventive medicine physician, I am periodically asked my thoughts on the current epidemic. So, here they are. You all know me. When I retired from the Navy in Dec 2019, I was the most senior preventive medicine physician on active duty in the Navy--maybe anywhere in DoD. Residency was more than 18 years in the rear-view mirror. One of the things prev med physicians do is risk communication. Some people say I do it poorly, but nobody can say I do it inaccurately. To illustrate that distinction, a short true story. In 1993 I was assigned as Battalion Surgeon, 1st Bn, 8th Marines. We had gone ashore in Egypt for Bright Star ’93 and then redeployed to the USS Guadalcanal Amphibious Ready Group after completion of the exercise. A few days after returning to the ship, my CO called me to his stateroom. I walked in, and the Lieutenant Colonel was laying on his rack, clearly feverish. Fever by oral temp was >102F. Moved the CO to ship’s medical dept., where he continued to be febrile and became progressively jaundiced. Pertinent history included a night of attack by biting insects while ashore in Egypt, so I knew he had an arbovirus. Blood sent off for assay came back negative for everything a couple months later, so I was flying by seat of clinical pants at the time. I knew from his general signs and symptoms constellation that there was no specific treatment for him, and although he was very ill, he was holding his own—no need to medevac to an ICU. He asked me, one day, “Am I going to make it?” My reply was, “Published data say I don’t have more than a 3% chance of losing you, Sir!” I’m not sure he liked that answer. So now, CoVID-19. That’s the name of the disease. The name of the virus is SARS CoV-2. We now have a lot of data on this ‘pandemic.’ I’ll jump to the bottom line. The Centers for Disease Control’s recent published data places the mortality rate for symptomatic cases at .004, or 4 per thousand. But that is just the symptomatic cases, and the CDC estimates an asymptomatic rate of 35%. If we inflate the symptomatic denominator to include the asymptomatic denominator, that makes the all infections mortality rate .0026. But, the population based antibody studies recently done by Stanford University indicates a 50%, not a 35% asymptomatic rate. That would drop the all infections mortality rate to .002. So, where does a mortality rate of .002 fall in the general scheme of things? Well, the accepted all infections mortality rate for seasonal influenza is .001. That means that according to the best data we have now, this bat virus is a whopping twice as lethal as the seasonal flu. The ‘whopping’ was sarsastic. At that level, a factor of two is either statistically insignificant, or if it is, we would call that a distinction without a difference. Does social distancing have a benefit? Not in my eyes. What it does do is preserve a density of susceptibles in the population that is capable of ongoing transmission. If we have a big surge this fall and winter as respiratory virus transmission goes up, it will be because all those ‘socially responsible’ people preserved their ability to acquire and transmit the virus, when we could have all be establishing herd immunity since there is no vaccine. Stanford’s population studies in CA found that half the people who tested positive had no idea they’d ever been infected, and a large fraction of the remainder had a few days of headache and/or mild fever. Yup, that’s what we destroyed the economy over. My other criticism of the whole lockdown is that people advocating it have attentional bandwidth only for one independent variable (daily number of social contacts) and one dependent variable (the R0, or number of secondary cases generated by each case). When R0 is greater than 1, an epidemic expands; when it is less than 1, it contracts. This virus never had a large R0. So, while some are dislocating their shoulders patting themselves on the back for ‘doing good,’ we have seen measurable upticks in deaths related to alcohol abuse, suicides due to depression caused by isolation, suicides due to despondency over destroyed livelihoods, and probably a few other measurable causes. We have logically had unmeasurable upticks in mortality due to cancellation of all elective procedures, as if these would have had no impact on health. We have cancelled preventive medicine screenings for cancers and other conditions, logically increasing mortality from these other conditions, although we will never be able to see that in the statistics. Bottom line, the lockdown cheerleaders don’t care what anyone dies of as long as it’s not SARS CoV-2. Then we come to our inflated death statistics, which are a large part of what drives current policy. It used to be that death certificates were based on evidence and reasonable clinical suspicion. No longer, at least not for SARS CoV-2. This is all (truncated)

One of the letters I wrote to Trudeau. Feel free to copy and send if you want. 😊 June 23, 2020 Dear Prime Minister Trudeau, As a Canadian, I am deeply concerned about the future of our amazing country. Canadians are suffering. Business owners are losing their livelihoods, families are losing their loved ones to illness and suicide, children’s futures are looking bleak. For the last five years we have watched as our government gave away billions in “aid”, while we have thousands upon thousands of Canadians who are living in poverty, many are homeless, struggling with mental illness and/or addiction, with no help in sight. No one seems to be able to give an answer about how much money was spent on the failed campaign for the temporary seat on the United Nations Security Council, and the $2.3 million reported by the media is likely a fraction of the true cost. We have first nations people who don’t have access to the most basic need; clean water. Their infrastructure has been planned and built to the lowest standards and outputs. Grassy Narrows is suffering from generations of exposure to mercury that a paper mill was allowed to dump into the river upstream from them. They are still suffering to this day. In 2020 it is unconscionable that any Canadian does not have clean water. Our media has been corrupted through government funding and “bail outs”. We were astounded to hear that big, profitable corporations were being given millions of dollars, while our seniors receive a paltry pension of $1200 a month or less after paying into the Canadian Pension Plan for decades. Our healthcare system is broken and our education system is failing our youth. It is time for massive changes. Our system of government is not working for the betterment of Canadians and it has not for decades. One of the main promises you ran on was election reform and another promise has been broken. When you ran for Prime Minister, your slogan was “Real Change. (Now) A Canada that Works. Together.” Except that right now a lot of Canadians are not working at all and the provinces haven’t worked together for a long time. Real Change. Now. In parliament. Our government needs to be dissolved and a new system, one that puts Canadians first, needs to be built to replace it. Do the right thing Prime Minister Trudeau. Either put Canadians first in every decision or resign.

column36:
Something you didn't know about "CASH". 

Alot of people don't see what's coming with how the government is pushing towards a cashless society. Especially with the ramp up of Covid-19. This should be worrying alot of you who understand commerce. We should be fighting for our right to use cash as a legal tender more often.

Why cashless society is the worst thing for us all.
Cash is the most liquid asset and can be used immediately to perform economic actions like buying, selling, or paying debt, and meeting immediate wants and needs. 
Once you have no hold of physical currency, the control of your invisible cash is in the hands of the banking institutions and government. Without cash, your control over your immediate assets becomes a digital illusion that can be controlled and manipulated as seen fit by the banks as well as the governments. 
The government and banks can reserve the right to hold on to, postpone or lock your available funds in case of pandemic, economical crash, civil war, protests, refusal to co-operate, tax, refusal to be vaccinated, even if the government or the banks are illegally operating.  
The idea of you having control over your money is just an illusion. The profiteers are the banks and by any means necessary, the banks will manipulate, bribe and pay off politicians to pass the law or regulation of the reduction of cash flow? Why?

Every physical penny that you hold in your pocket represents your control and your power of economic circulation, growth and exchange of goods. Once you are no longer in possession of physical currency, your bank is. 
The dream of every bank is to have full access, holdings and control of your money. This money becomes their borrowing and lending power.  (E.g. 2009 US Bank Bail out. (Movie Big Short is about this crisis).

Banks charge you fees to safe hold your money. They also charge you transaction fees and withdrawal fees. Fees, fees, fees whilst they have your money and operate with it. Shouldn't it be the other way around?? 
Point is, if bank has your cash, the bank has control. I've noticed a huge reductions in cash handling for apparent reason of reducing the spread of covid-19. Really?? So it's ok for the sales assistant to handle your shopping goods, your groceries, pack your bags, pass you the bag and the receipt but it's not ok to handle your cash? Absolutely incredible bullshit. 
Use your cash, it's against the law for anyone to refuse the cash payment in exchange for goods and services. 
Take back the control of your life.

You think masks aren’t dangerous? 

We keep a Pulse Ox in my purse to measure Ella’s O2 levels for when she has asthma flare ups.... 

We decided to do a little experiment... 

Art first.... 

He started at 98% with a heart rate of 78.... 

He wore the mask for TWO minutes..... 

His Oxygen level dropped to 89% and his heart rate went up to 82.... 

In TWO minutes.... 

And he touched his face approximately 6 times because the mask itches... 🤦🏻‍♀️ 

So, next we tried Ella and I recorded it.... 

You can see the video in the post below 👇🏼

She started at 99% Oxygen level and a heart rate of 89.... 

In less than a minute she jumped up to a heart rate of 106 😳 and her Oxygen dropped to 95.... 

You can see the last few seconds of the video she’s trying to take a deep breath and I can see her O2 drop so I stopped the video and took the mask off. 

This is so not safe or healthy for anyone.... Let alone children. 

Remember this when they are trying to mandate your kids wear a mask at school. 

Neither one of them even got up off the couch 😧

column35: West Haven Police Department
column36:
The attached video was taken by a citizen who was observing the event as it developed.
The location of the incident was the Bradly Point shore area.  
At approximately 1256 hours, we received numerous 911 calls for a person in distress and then eventually a report of a person in the water struggling to stay afloat.  
All shore patrol units and area beat cars were dispatched to the area.  Several units arrived at the same time and upon observing and assessing the situation it was determined the subject in the water was in immediate danger of going under if he was not given assistance.
Given the life threatening situation at hand, one of our Officers made the critical decision to remove his gear and then entered the water from the rocks to make his way toward the distressed male party.   He swam out for a considerable distance, approximately 100 yards, before making it to the male who was clearly struggling to stay afloat by the rock jetty.  The first Officer then began to drag the male back towards the shoreline while swimming against the current.  
While making their way back to shore a second Officer entered the water and joined up with the two to assist with the rescue.
Upon making it to shore the male was pulled up the rocks and assisted up the uneven shoreline by Officers waiting on scene.  
The FD and AMR arrived and treated the male on scene.  
No injuries were reported to have occurred to the Officers who assisted in this rescue.
Water Safety Reminder: Always be mindful of the power of the water in the sound including changing tides and undercurrents. Know your limits and even if you are a strong swimmer go out with a buddy or swim where you can be seen by others. We want everyone to enjoy the beach and the warm water but please do so SAFELY.

column31: #REPOST Original post by Silvia Valdman My Dear Friends, please share this letter widely, on social media (outside FB as well), media outlets, MPPs, MPs etc. This is a very important matter that will affect all of us at some point. RE: Access to Patient Mr. Suhar Valdman, Welland Hospital 65 Third St. Welland ON L3B 4W6 To Whom It May Concern, June 22,2020 Mr. Suhar Valdman is currently a patient in your hospital. His wife, Mrs. Valdman was given a paltry 30 min window to spend with her beloved husband today. She requested more time to feed him lunch and was denied. Mr. Valdman’s only daughter Silvia, was informed by hospital staff that she will not be allowed to see her father unless he is on his death bed. Silvia and I represent a large group of activists in Canada. We are horrified by the draconian policy of this hospital and many other hospitals in Ontario under the pretext of patient safety. This is especially perplexing given the memorandum issued on June 15 by Dr. David Williams (Chief Medical Officer of Health). Dr. Williams recommended that all public and private hospitals allow visitations from family and caregivers. According to Dr. Williams, “Visits from family and caregivers and other visitors contribute greatly to a patient’s quality of life and well-being.” Let’s examine the data. According to the CDC, the infection fatality rate from COVID-19 is 0.26% and likely lower as up to 80% of cases are mild or asymptomatic. According to the WHO there is no evidence of asymptomatic transmission of the SarsCov2 virus. There is a well documented study to support this as well as other anecdotal studies. 63% of deaths in Ontario occurred in Long Term Care Facilities (LTCFs). It is important to heed these deaths in Ontario’s LTCF and elucidate their causes. On May 20, Brigadier General Commander C.J.J. Mialkowski submitted a gruesome report on five of Ontario’s LTCFs. The details are overt in proving that neglect and abuse of the residents was rampant. Here are some of the disturbing details: -verbal abuse and aggressive behaviour by caretakers -significant gross fecal contamination -insect infestation -delayed changing of soiled residents -forceful feeding and hydration causing audible chocking /aspiration -patients crying for help with staff not responding until after 30 min to 2 hours -residents not bathed for several weeks Would these conditions have festered if these vulnerable residents were allowed to have visitation from family members? In addition, the report states the following: “NO psychosocial support for these residents who have all of a sudden had their families taken away, anxiety and depression being treated with narcotics and benzodiazepenes to sedate them.” Residents reported to have felt, “Scared and feel alone like they’re in jail.” Despite wide-spread knowledge of this report Welland Hospital is refusing Mr. Valdman the love and care of his wife and daughter during the most vulnerable time in his life. Mr. Valdman survived the Nazi occupation in Romania. Now, nearing the end of his life he is the victim of medical tyranny. The extreme stress and anxiety of his immediate family is a consequence of his unjust treatment. Furthermore, in the complex matter of advocating for a patient’s rights, and treatment decisions, it is very difficult to do so remotely, family members need to be able to assess the patient in person and discuss matters with care providers in person. We have read the accounts of many people whose loved ones died in isolation deprived of love, care and compassion. Is this not a crime against humanity? How many people in Ontario hospitals and LTCFs have died alone? We demand the immediate access to Mr. Valdman by his beloved wife and daughter. They are both willing to wear PPE at the standard of other workers in the hospital who have access to patients. We look forward to a quick resolution of this matter. Sincerely, Dr. Jasmine Gilani and Silvia Valdman, LL.B. Silvia Valdman’s cell: 289-241-1000

column35: We The People Rally
column36:
We the people of Oregon shall rise up and have our voices heard.

June 24th is the first day of the special session being called by Governor Brown. 
Many Oregonians have been hurt by the executive orders in place since March and are not being heard. 

Schedule:

7am - 8am- optional sign waving at the entrance to the garage where legislators enter. We will have some signs available to use. We will be standing outside the garage entrance to let our legislators know we are there.

9am -  Rally starts. Stay as long as you like! Wave signs, flags and make your voices heard.  We've heard they may have a listening area for the floor & committee sessions outside the Capitol.

FAQ:

What should I bring?

Bring lots of water as it will be warm and there will not be services or anyone allowed in the Capitol. Bring food, sunscreen, hats, and signs. Please clean up after yourself and take out everything you bring and leave the area cleaner than when you arrived. 

Where should I park?

There is paid parking around the Capitol and in the underground lot. These are all paid spots, so you may need to return to feed your meter. More on parking: https://www.oregon.gov/das/FleetPark/Pages/maps.aspx

Is there a bathroom?

Yes, there will be a porta potty near the rally we have provided.

Do I need to wear a mask?

The executive order that goes into effect on 6/24 for seven counties (including Marion) is for indoor mask use. Our event is outdoors. However, we encourage you to wear a mask if that is your preference.

In short it means all Banks can take your cash from your bank account(s) if they fold. ✅ Last Thursday, the Australian Senate referred the Banking Amendment (Deposits) Bill 2020 to the Senate Economics Legislation Committee for a public inquiry. Add your voice please over the next few weeks to End “Bail- In” Laws This legislation, which was introduced into the Australian Senate by One Nation Senator Malcolm Roberts, would amend the Banking Act 1959 and eliminate any risk to retail bank deposits being subject to bail-in (or forced confiscation) by Authorised Deposit-taking Institutions (ADIs) operating in Australia. Martin North and John Adams released a new episode on their YouTube channel, In the Interests of the People, where they provide detail about the inquiry. You can watch their show here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qEw5x-Yg8Fk Submissions to the inquiry close on 10 July 2020 and the committee is required to report back to the Australian Senate by 10 August 2020. More information about the inquiry can be found at the following link: https://www.aph.gov.au/Parliamentary_Business/Committees/Senate/Economics/BankingDeposits I would encourage you to participate in the inquiry by: making a submission to the inquiry; making your federal MP and senators aware of the Banking Amendment (Deposits) Bill 2020 and that you encourage them to support the passage of the legislation through the Federal Parliament. I would also encourage you to speak to your friends and family about the issue of bail-in and educate them on the subject. Tell them that there is an effort underway in Federal Parliament to eliminate the risk of retail bank deposits being bailed-in in Australia. Unfortunately, many Australians believe that the bail-in of retail bank deposits is some sort of conspiracy theory and that there is zero chance of it ever occurring in Australia. It is critical that we make these people understand that the bail-in of retail bank deposits has already occurred in Australia and therefore the issue shouldn’t be treated lightly. As noted in their previous show, It’s Too Late – Bail-in Has Already Happened, published on 20 March 2019 (see the following link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b8CD2hNP8Uc&t=6s), bail-in of retail bank deposits occurred in Melbourne in 1892 and 1893 during the economic depression of the 1890s (although the process was called ‘reconstruction’). Just like with the fight on the $10,000 cash transaction ban (which is still yet to be resolved one way or the other). John is chasing the Federal Government on this issue), a huge effort is required by ordinary Australians to ram the message through to the politicians that they need to enact legislation which is in the people’s interests and not in the interests of the elite establishment. Any help which you can provide in the coming 3 to 4 weeks would be most welcomed. Please copy, paste and share on your timeline, in groups, all over social media and with everyone you know, we need everyone to participate in this. We must stop bail in of our bank deposits before it's too late. Read the post and do something about it Financial Sector Legislation Amendment (Crisis Resolution Powers And Other Measures) Bill 2017 was passed into law.

column31: My Dear Friends, please share this letter widely, on social media (outside FB as well), media outlets, MPPs, MPs etc. This is a very important matter that will affect all of us at some point. RE: Access to Patient Mr. Suhar Valdman, Welland Hospital 65 Third St. Welland ON L3B 4W6 To Whom It May Concern, June 22,2020 Mr. Suhar Valdman is currently a patient in your hospital. His wife, Mrs. Valdman was given a paltry 30 min window to spend with her beloved husband today. She requested more time to feed him lunch and was denied. Mr. Valdman’s only daughter Silvia, was informed by hospital staff that she will not be allowed to see her father unless he is on his death bed. Silvia and I represent a large group of activists in Canada. We are horrified by the draconian policy of this hospital and many other hospitals in Ontario under the pretext of patient safety. This is especially perplexing given the memorandum issued on June 15 by Dr. David Williams (Chief Medical Officer of Health). Dr. Williams recommended that all public and private hospitals allow visitations from family and caregivers. According to Dr. Williams, “Visits from family and caregivers and other visitors contribute greatly to a patient’s quality of life and well-being.” Let’s examine the data. According to the CDC, the infection fatality rate from COVID-19 is 0.26% and likely lower as up to 80% of cases are mild or asymptomatic. According to the WHO there is no evidence of asymptomatic transmission of the SarsCov2 virus. There is a well documented study to support this as well as other anecdotal studies. 63% of deaths in Ontario occurred in Long Term Care Facilities (LTCFs). It is important to heed these deaths in Ontario’s LTCF and elucidate their causes. On May 20, Brigadier General Commander C.J.J. Mialkowski submitted a gruesome report on five of Ontario’s LTCFs. The details are overt in proving that neglect and abuse of the residents was rampant. Here are some of the disturbing details: -verbal abuse and aggressive behaviour by caretakers -significant gross fecal contamination -insect infestation -delayed changing of soiled residents -forceful feeding and hydration causing audible chocking /aspiration -patients crying for help with staff not responding until after 30 min to 2 hours -residents not bathed for several weeks Would these conditions have festered if these vulnerable residents were allowed to have visitation from family members? In addition, the report states the following: “NO psychosocial support for these residents who have all of a sudden had their families taken away, anxiety and depression being treated with narcotics and benzodiazepenes to sedate them.” Residents reported to have felt, “Scared and feel alone like they’re in jail.” Despite wide-spread knowledge of this report Welland Hospital is refusing Mr. Valdman the love and care of his wife and daughter during the most vulnerable time in his life. Mr. Valdman survived the Nazi occupation in Romania. Now, nearing the end of his life he is the victim of medical tyranny. The extreme stress and anxiety of his immediate family is a consequence of his unjust treatment. Furthermore, in the complex matter of advocating for a patient’s rights, and treatment decisions, it is very difficult to do so remotely, family members need to be able to assess the patient in person and discuss matters with care providers in person. We have read the accounts of many people whose loved ones died in isolation deprived of love, care and compassion. Is this not a crime against humanity? How many people in Ontario hospitals and LTCFs have died alone? We demand the immediate access to Mr. Valdman by his beloved wife and daughter. They are both willing to wear PPE at the standard of other workers in the hospital who have access to patients. We look forward to a quick resolution of this matter. Sincerely, Dr. Jasmine Gilani and Silvia Valdman, LL.B. Silvia Valdman’s cell: 289-241-1000

For all you mask wearers (especially those of you who think wearing it outside is NOT stupid) I know I’m about to burst your “google doctor degree” bubble, but here goes nothing : So Masks?

I am OSHA 10 certified. I know some of you are too. I don’t really know WHY OSHA hasn’t come forward and stopped the nonsense BUT I want to cover three things
• N95 masks and masks with exhale ports
• surgical masks
• filter or cloth masks
Okay, so upon further inspection, OSHA says some masks are okay and not okay in certain situations.
If you’re working with fumes and aerosol chemicals and you give your employees the wrong masks and they get sick, you can be sued.
• N95 masks: are designed for CONTAMINATED environments. That means when you exhale through N95 the design is that you are exhaling into contamination. The exhale from N95 masks are vented to breath straight out without filtration. They don’t filter the air on the way out. They don’t need to.
Conclusion: if you’re in Target and the guy with Covid has a N95 mask, his covid breath is unfiltered being exhaled into Target (because it was designed for already contaminated environments, it’s not filtering your air on the way out).
• Surgical Mask: these masks were designed and approved for STERILE environments. The amount of particles and contaminants in the outside and indoor environments where people are CLOGGING these masks very, VERY quickly. The moisture from your breath combined with the clogged mask will render it “useless” IF you come in contact with Covid and your mask traps it, YOU become a walking virus dispenser. Everytime you put your mask on you are breathing the germs from EVERYWHERE you went. They should be changed or thrown out every “20-30 minutes in a non sterile environment.”
• Cloth masks: I can’t even believe I’m having to explain this, but here it goes. Today, three people pointed to their masks as they walked by me entering Lowe’s. They said “ya gotta wear your mask BRO” I said very clearly “those masks don’t work bro, in fact they MAKE you sicker” they “pshh’d” me. By now hopefully you all know CLOTH masks do not filter anything. You mean the American flag one my aunt made? Yes. The one with sunflowers that looks so cute? Yes. The bandanna, the cut up t-shirt, the scarf ALL of them offer NO FILTERING whatsoever. As you exhale, you are ridding your lungs of contaminants and carbon dioxide. Cloth masks trap this carbon dioxide the best. It actually risks your health, rather than protect it. The moisture caught in these masks can become mildew ridden over night. Dry coughing, enhanced allergies, sore throat are all symptoms of a micro-mold in your mask.
-Ultimate Answer:
*N95 blows the virus into the air from a contaminated person.
*The surgical mask is not designed for the outside world and will not filter the virus upon inhaling through it. It’s filtration works on the exhale, (Like a vacuum bag, it only works one way) but likely stops after 20 minutes, rendering it useless outside of a STERILE ENVIRONMENT (correct Becky, they don’t work in a bar, not even a little bit).
*Cloth masks are WORSE than none. It’s equivalent to using a chain link fence to stop mosquitos.
The CDC wants us to keep wearing masks. The masks don’t work. They’re being used to provide false comfort and push forward a specific agenda. For the love of God, research each mask’s designed use and purpose, I bet you will find NONE are used in the way of “viral defense.”
Just like EVERY Flu season kids, wash your hands. Sanitize your hands. Don’t touch stuff. Sanitize your phone. Don’t touch people. And keep your distance. Why? Because your breath stinks, your deodorant is failing, your shoes are old and stink, that shirts not clean, & I like my space. Trust me I can hear you from here. Lots of reasons to keep your distance and work on body hygiene. But trust me, the masks do not work.
*Occupational Safety & Hazard Association sited.
The top American organization for safety.
They regulate and educate asbestos workers, surgical rooms, you name it.
I know, facts suck. They throw a wrench into the perfectly (seeming) packaged pill you are willingly swallowing. Facts make you have to form your OWN OPINION, instead of regurgitating someone else’s, and I know how uncomfortable that makes a lot of you. If your mask gives you security, by all means wear it. Just know it is a false sense of security and you shouldn’t shame anyone into partaking in such “conspiracies.”
If select politicians stopped enforcing it, no one would continue this nonsense. Don’t drink the kool-aid!
Janet Sue Colvard

Hi guys! So I was just denied entry into a local store (where there are no mandates for mask wearing) I emailed the store and I think we all should when/if we are denied access. Businesses need to be aware not everyone is comfortable with mask wearing. Below is a copy of my email, along with supporting evidence from WHO showing the potential harms/ disadvantages of mask wearing for healthy people in general population. It is a great resource to have/use. Feel free to use my email as a template/guideline. Hi there, I am a regular customer at the (STORE). I came into the store today and was denied entry as I did not feel comfortable wearing a mask. I don’t mind being asked but it is only recommended by the Government of Canada that masked be worn when physical distancing is not possible. The store was empty and you have provided plexiglass shields at the register which would allow me, as a customer, to maintain social distancing. The World Health Organization issued guidelines for mask wearing June 8, 2020. I have attached the link below. https://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/handle/10665/332293/WHO-2019-nCov-IPC_Masks-2020.4-eng.pdf I would like to bring your attention specifically to page 8 of the document under, “Potential harms/disadvantages” of mask use in healthy people in the general population. Here you will find many reason why I am uncomfortable wearing a mask and why it should always be OPTIONAL. I don’t mind being asked to wear one but it should be my choice. To me the potential harms and disadvantages of wearing a mask out weigh the advantages especially when social distancing is possible. I hope you will realize that making mask mandatory is not something all customers feel comfortable doing and hope the supporting evidence in the document will be taken into consideration. Thank you.

Legitimacy of Covid19 ( SARS-Cov-2) vaccine:

Let me see if I understand this correctly...
The SARS coronavirus of 2003 is an infection for which, over the past 17 years, no vaccine could be made. It was not possible, and the attempts were deadly when they tried.
In the history of medical science, no vaccine has ever been able to be made for any coronaviruses. Not ever. There is not a single one in existence.
However, somehow, in 4 months, Oxford University in the United Kingdom, with $750,000,000 of Bill and Melinda Gates’ Foundation money, have developed a vaccine, completed the first phase clinical trial, and now as they move to human trials, these trials on 2000 humans are going to be conducted in Brazil, outside of the oversight of North American or British Health regulators?
And better yet, it is already being produced by AstraZeneca, a pharmaceutical company with a criminal rap sheet that includes:
2003, pled guilty to illegal marketing of their prostate cancer drug and paid a $64,000,000 criminal fine, a $266,000,000 civil lawsuit for false claims, and a $25,000,000 fine for Medicaid fraud.
2004, AstraZeneca was sued in California and Massachusetts for false advertising, for claiming one of their own drugs that was going out of patent was not as good as their new drug even though it appears to be the same thing. And believe it or not, those cases are still before the courts. They have drug it out for 16 years.
2004, AstraZeneca received a warning letter from the FDA for lying in their advertisements about FDA endorsement.
In 2010, AstraZeneca was fined $520,000,000 because it is a legally marketed one of its antipsychotic drugs for nonapproved uses and committed Medicaid fraud to the tune of $218,000,000
In 2002, AstraZeneca was forced to put more warning labels on their lung cancer drug after several patients died of pneumonia because of their drugs.
In 2003, the University of Illinois studied their schizophrenia drug and found undeclared risks of developing diabetes as a result of taking the drugs, which ultimately led to a $198,000,000 settlement.
In 2004, AstraZeneca faced criticism by public watchdog groups about the severe side effects of their Crestor drug compared to other cholesterol drugs, and in 2005, Tufts University completed a clinical study identifying the accuracy of the claims by the watchdog groups. This is still ongoing, 16 years later.
In 2001, AstraZeneca had to pay another pharmaceutical $21,000,000, for knowingly and intentionally trying to keep a competitive drug generic drug off the market.
In 2003, AstraZeneca was fined €60,000,000 by the European Commission for misusing patent rules and lying on patents to protect its drugs from generic competitors.
In 2007, AstraZeneca had to pay a $12.9 million criminal judgment for unfairly and deceptively overcharging Medicaid and insurance companies for a prostate cancer drug.
In 2010, AstraZeneca paid $103,000,000 to settle a federal lawsuit for Medicaid fraud for asthma medications.
In 2009, AstraZeneca had to pay $2.6 million for Medicaid fraud.

column34: Things are not as they seem. WILL YOU BE BRAVE ENOUGH TO SEE THE DIFFERENCE?
column35: Kayla
column36:
You might want to sit down for this:

-In the 2018/19 flu season in our country, 8676 people died from the flu. INCLUDING children.

-THIS season however, 8174 people died in 2019/20 of Coronavirus in our country.

-6620 of those deaths were from nursing homes! Many of which were found with such poor hygienic practices, our MILITARY had to take full control over the homes. Hygienic practices so poor that the same gloves were used for multiple patients, beds had no linen due to no laundry being done, these same employees travelled from one nursing home or group home to another.

-That leaves 1553 total in Canada who died of Covid. Many of THESE numbers came from institutions such as mental health centres, prisons, and jails. We actually have no comparative studies from our government publicly. AKA: no transparency. 

-Not one of the deaths have had autopsies. Did they die of Covid? Did they die of other diseases and just happened to HAVE Covid? Nobody actually is telling us. But what we do know is that report after report of people entering the hospital for things like heart attack was marked down as Covid on their charts. So did 1553 people actually die of Covid?

-ZERO of these deaths were children under the age of 19. ZERO!

-This leaves the general public with a 0.00004% chance of dying of Covid so far this year. 

What. have. we. done?

-0.00004%. Do you know what that even means? If not, you might want to look at your chances of dying for every other illness in Canada. 

-Ready for this one? We have had the lowest number of flu reported this year than ANY OTHER YEAR FOR THE PAST NINE YEARS!!! NINE YEARS! Where did Influenza A and B go all of a sudden? 

-But Dawna, you are killing my grandma and grandpa!! 
Listen, people are scared. I completely get it. I was so afraid for my 70 year old mother that I was angry she didn't listen to me when she decided to go on a cruise ship in February/March of this year. I called every day to see if she was sick or dead and would have been COMPLETELY mad if I saw anyone even BREATHING too close to her. Yet she was fine. In fact everyone on her cruise was fine. She has lived her life ever since and is fine. Is she just one person? Of course. But she represents the over 99% with the exact. same. story.

I've watched the news. They get paid to scare. you. They. get. paid. to. scare. you. 

But read the above stats again. If your grandma and grandpa are in a nursing home or hospital or long term mental health facility then yes, they have a higher chance there. Typically though, only the ones where hygiene practices are not followed properly and where aerosol equipment (like ventilators) are being used and cause Covid to actually be airborne. But in the general public they still only have a 0.00004% chance of dying from this virus. 

-Remember, Covid numbers are VERY different than covid deaths. Do not be alarmed when the dark and scary music comes on our mainstream media outlets, telling you there's another outbreak because the numbers are rising. They are simply testing more people and the labs are catching up with tests from weeks ago.
 
-Always ask yourself these questions when you hear of "Covid deaths:"
Was it confirmed that they died FROM Covid or WITH Covid?
Where did they contract it from? 
Was it in the general public, from someone in their own house, or a nursing home? 

Notice they never tell you?

*************************************************************************

Now, let's talk about masks. A big topic. a big debate now, right?

The biggest sadness in all of this, and what should make all of us rethink how we are approaching this topic, is allowing the misinformation to cause SUCH division and anger amongst each other. 

If you have merely looked at a title/conclusion of a news source, you have not earned the right to judge anyone. This is such an important distinction and one I urge you to consider from here on out. Unless you have unbiased scientific literature from recent empirical study, then you have NO RIGHT to turn your 'opinion' into all out accusations of pre-meditated murder. No right. This is the biggest atrocity in our society - And one of the main reasons I write to you today. 

The news has turned you against each other. The government is allowing people to move into Phase 2 and 3, yet the news wants you to believe that it is STILL unsafe to go out. The STAY HOME SAVE LIVES signs, even outside some of our local Fire Department, have created a culture of stay home or you are going to die or worse... you are a murderer.  

What. have. we. done?

You have a right to wear your mask and keep your distance and no one wants to take away your right to do what you feel is right and safe for you based on your own research. If you are vulnerable, by all means keep your distance. To this day I keep my 6 feet distance because I know how you fear. I may be against the fear. But I am not against you. 

The problem is in your accusations. (truncated)

column35: Ohio Advocates for Medical Freedom
column36:
“Ohio Department of Health Interim Director Lance Himes has officially signed an order allowing county fairs and animal exhibits to be held this summer.”

“The order states that county fairs are allowed to open as long as safety measures to prevent the spread of the COVID-19 coronavirus are followed.”

“Food vendors must follow the same guidelines as restaurants, which includes social distancing for those in line, no self-serve areas, and six feet of space between seating.”

“In order for a fair to have amusement rides, it must follow all order from the Ohio Department of Health and the Ohio Department of Agriculture.”

It appears that the health department is now making an attempt to appease the citizens of Ohio by allowing Fair’s to operate this summer. ￼￼
But how are fairs actually going to operate under the heath department’s draconian social distancing policies?

We all know that fairs are places with few crowds that rarely have lengthy lines with people pushed together like sardines waiting for a frosty lemonade on a hot day￼. (Biting sarcasm)

Are you going to be willing to stand in the funnel cake line if it reaches into the next county? ￼

How many mom and pop food trucks are going to be able to afford the additional costs for cleaners, plexiglass, additional condiment serving supplies  due to the removal of self-serve stations? ￼￼
If they are able, who’s paying for those additional costs? 
How much more will you be paying for those food items?￼

How in the world is social distancing going to work on rides?￼ 
If people are required to space out on Rides that’s going to mean they have to run the rides more often￼￼ to accommodate the same number of fair goers. 
Again, Who pays for the additional cost of running the rides? 
Do we honestly believe those costs aren’t going to trickle down to the Ohio￼￼ans who are already suffering financially and just want to be able to take their family on an enjoyable outing this summer? 
You bet they will.

Governor Dewine in the Ohio health department are out of touch with reality. The death rate is less than a half a percent and we have had no massive spikes in the infection. ￼￼￼This is about maintaining a visual presence of fear in our communities. 

Let’s be real. 
Nobody goes to the fair because they’re looking for a sterile environment to enjoy themselves. 
You go to the fair knowing full well you’re probably going to be introducing your body to a host of new bacteria and viruses (that will likely improve your immune system). 
You’re there to let the kids get down in the dirt, pet the animals, and take a chance on rides that were probably put together in less than 24 hours and missing a bolt or two￼. 

Life is all about risks. 

Let those that want to live, live. 

If you’re afraid of Covid, then don’t go to the fair￼. 

Ohio needs to be FULLY OPERATIONAL. 
The Health department needs to stop pretending that Ohio is really “open” under their extreme social distancing measures.

#FairsAreForFamiliesNotFear
#OpenOhioAllTheWay￼

Source: https://www.wdtn.com/statehouse-news/ohio-dept-of-health-director-signs-order-allowing-fairs-this-summer/

——-

Join OAMF in fighting the overreaching orders of this governor and his director of health: www.facebook.com/groups/RestoreOhio

And please consider a small donation to allow us to continue to server you and your liberty: www.ohioamf.org/donate

The state is genocidal. From Kathy Sloan...
"MASS MURDER BY THE STATE. If this doesn't fill you with rage, nothing will."

Julianne Jaz...
"I just read an article earlier today about *nursing home deaths* in Sweden, which is what was comparable to the US. And like the US and Canada, Sweden put into place new policies that added - for the first time ever - "age" to the list of considerations for who should be designated DNR - Do Not Resuscitate.
It IS absolutely possible to track policies implemented and actions taken to discern what is happening here.
Here's a list of what was done here in the US that deliberately caused the deaths of a minimum of 40K people:
Governors mandated moving actively ill Covid-19 patients into rooms (and facilities, i.e. nursing homes) with residents who were NOT ill.
Upon arrival at either the hospital or nursing home, the patient was immediately separated from their family members, and "no contact orders" made sure those families would never see the patient alive again.
Once the patient was isolated and without anyone to act as their advocate, they were told the best possible treatment would be to immediately intubate them and put them on ventilators. Patients were NOT offered alternative treatments, e.g., hydroxychloroquine and zinc.
In order to be intubated, the patients were given up to 10 different narcotics and paralytics, which rendered them incapable of requesting that either the treatment be modified or removed.nn
Once on a ventilator, staff were informed ANYONE on a ventilator was DNR - Do Not Resuscitate, regardless of anything the patient, or their family, might have said.
At that point, the only thing left to do was tie these nearly lifeless people to their beds and wait for the ventilators to do their job - i.e., destroying the patient's lungs - because the treatment was completely INAPPROPRIATE AND UNNECESSARY.
Once those things happened, Medicare reimbursements went from $13K (no ventilator) to $39K (with ventilator).
Oh, there are two last pieces - 1) each one of the Governors of these 8 states (with the very highest death rates) provided the corporations owning the nursing homes and hospitals where these protocols were implemented FULL INDEMNIFICATION against any injuries or wrongful death lawsuits, and 2) Coroners were instructed they must remove the bodies in under 60 minutes, death certificates were completed by personnel who never treated the patient, or autopsied them post expiration, and the bodies were buried ASAP in mass graves, often in "Potter's Field" circumstances, so the likelihood of being able to exhume their bodies for any kind of forensic examination was completely lost.
From the time these patients were separated from their families, they were murdered and disposed of and their families were given no recourse other than acquiescence to the entire atrocity, which most assuredly constitutes a crime against humanity.
IT IS POSSIBLE TO KNOW WHAT'S HAPPENING. But you have to be willing to educate yourself and follow the work of credible sources of information, e.g. James Corbett (The Corbett Report), Rosemary Frei (Off Guardian), Derek Broze (The Last American Vagabond), Professor Dolores Cahill (Irish University professor), along with several others.
Isn't it worth it to know the truth?
Don't just throw up your hands and wail, "I can't possibly figure this out." THAT is exactly the place they want you to be."

column35: We The People Rally
column36:
We the people of Oregon shall rise up and have our voices heard.

June 24th is the first day of the special session being called by Governor Brown. 
Many Oregonians have been hurt by the executive orders in place since March and are not being heard. 

Schedule:

7am - 8am- optional sign waving at the entrance to the garage where legislators enter. We will have some signs available to use. We will be standing outside the garage entrance to let our legislators know we are there.

9am -  Rally starts. Stay as long as you like! Wave signs, flags and make your voices heard.  We've heard they may have a listening area for the floor & committee sessions outside the Capitol.

FAQ:

What should I bring?

Bring lots of water as it will be warm and there will not be services or anyone allowed in the Capitol. Bring food, sunscreen, hats, and signs. Please clean up after yourself and take out everything you bring and leave the area cleaner than when you arrived. 

Where should I park?

There is paid parking around the Capitol and in the underground lot. These are all paid spots, so you may need to return to feed your meter. More on parking: https://www.oregon.gov/das/FleetPark/Pages/maps.aspx

Is there a bathroom?

Yes, there will be a porta potty near the rally we have provided.

Do I need to wear a mask?

The executive order that goes into effect on 6/24 for seven counties (including Marion) is for indoor mask use. Our event is outdoors. However, we encourage you to wear a mask if that is your preference.

column31: Ok, if I’m understanding this correctly (and please help me understand better if I don’t), the thing with this new mandate is that they found a loophole so the governor can’t stop them. It’s left up to individual counties or whatever. The new mandate is that “businesses have to require masks for both employees and customers”, correct? The mandate is not that individuals have to wear a mask in public, it’s that the businesses now have to “require for you to wear them in their place of business or the business can be fined”. So, the business can refuse to serve you if you don’t have one on because they want to avoid fines. If you can’t ticket the people, make it impossible for them to get the things they need without complying. My question is... what can WE do? Yes, people on Facebook tell you to “claim a medical exemption”. And technically, I could claim this and most likely be proven right in a court of law. But now what? What happens when you want to go somewhere with your family? “We all have medical exemptions” isn’t going to fly eventually. Basically I’m saying, when enough people get called out on their “medical exemptions” that really don’t exist, they’re going to find a way to make you “prove” it. Then what? So what can we do? As individuals? As families? It’s not the businesses fault and they don’t want to be fined. This is just a bunch of BS! Now what!? Sure, I can avoid the counties around me that have this mandate. But, what happens when they all require it? Ideas??
