column31: I will be sending this to every member of my BOE and the State BOE tomorrow. I suggest you all do the same... AMERICAN ACADEMY OF PEDIATRICS SAYS SCHOOL CLOSURES HAVE BEEN HARMFUL, “STRONGLY ADVOCATES” FOR THEIR REOPENING by Kevin Ryan The American Academy of Pediatrics, the nation’s leading advocacy organization for children, representing 67​,000 pediatricians, has finally weighed in on the subject of schools, releasing a “Critical Update on COVID-19.” The group’s message to policy makers is clear: Reopen the schools. “The AAP strongly advocates that all policy considerations for the coming school year should start with a goal of having students physically present in school.” The organization, which publishes one of the most influential and widely-cited journals in all of science and medicine, says that the evidence shows that school shutdowns have been harmful to children. “There is already evidence of the negative impacts on children because of school closures in the spring of 2020.” “Lengthy time away from school and associated interruption of supportive services often results in social isolation, making it difficult for schools to identify and address important learning deficits as well as child and adolescent physical or sexual abuse, substance use, depression, and suicidal ideation. This, in turn, places children and adolescents at considerable risk of morbidity and, in some cases, mortality.” AAP also weighs in on the debate over whether schools and children are a major threat to the spread of COVID-19. “SARS-CoV-2 appears to behave differently in children and adolescents than other common respiratory viruses, such as influenza, on which much of the current guidance regarding school closures is based. Although children and adolescents play a major role in amplifying influenza outbreaks, to date, this does not appear to be the case with SARS-CoV-2.” “The preponderance of evidence indicates that children and adolescents are less likely to be symptomatic and less likely to have severe disease resulting from SARS-CoV-2 infection.” “In addition, children may be less likely to become infected and to spread infection.” The group also says that measures like the use of face coverings may not be “developmentally feasible” in the case of younger students if it “cannot be done safely (eg, the face covering makes wearers touch their face more than they otherwise would).” They recommend that “Schools may choose to not require their use when physical distancing measures can be effectively implemented.” But even if schools cannot maintain strict adherence to a 6-feet spacing rule, AAP recommends considering allowing closer distancing “if remote learning is the only alternative.” The overall message that the pediatricians are attempting to convey is one that seems to have been lost on politicians and policy makers during the COVID pandemic: the consequences of actions like school shutdowns must be considered in their entirety, not just with regards to preventing COVID transmission, in order to determine their benefit or harm. “Policies to mitigate the spread of COVID-19 within schools must be balanced with the known harms to children, adolescents, families, and the community by keeping children at home.” “Finally, policy makers should acknowledge that COVID-19 policies are intended to mitigate, not eliminate, risk.” SOURCES: https://services.aap.org/en/pages/2019-novel-coronavirus-covid-19-infections/clinical-guidance/covid-19-planning-considerations-return-to-in-person-education-in-schools/ https://www.aappublications.org/content/pediatrics-overview

column31: June 15, 2020 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE BUSINESS OWNERS, STATE SENATOR FILE LAWSUIT CHALLENGING LAMONT’S ‘NON-ESSENTIAL BUSINESS’ DESIGNATION Five small business owners and a sitting State Senator have filed a lawsuit challenging Governor Ned Lamont’s power to declare certain Connecticut businesses non-essential during the COVID-19 epidemic. “The public health crisis has resulted in an alarming expansion of executive power in our state,” said Joe Markley, director of the Connecticut Business Freedom Legal Fund, which is sponsoring the lawsuit. “It is essential that we define the limits of the governor’s power going forward, and we believe this lawsuit is the best way to settle the issue.” Plaintiffs in the lawsuit are Melanie Rivera-Maurice, owner of Gelled by Mel; Brandon Rocco, of Fearless Fitness; Christina Marshall, of Roots an Organic Salon; Darin Reisler of Plus One Defense Systems; Chad Lockhart, of Hartford County Tattoo; and State Senator Rob Sampson, a Realtor from Wolcott. “I recognize that Governor Lamont has had to make truly difficult decisions during this crisis,” Senator Sampson said. “However, over time it has become clear he has shifted from addressing legitimate public health concerns to advancing a political policy agenda. Many of his executive orders constitute overreaches of his authority which must be challenged. “My neighbors are not subjects but American citizens, and they deserve to be treated as such. I am proud to stand with fellow business owners who have suffered tremendously as a result of unfair and arbitrary decisions. I’m confident the court will recognize that it is not within the governor’s power to determine which businesses are essential, and to demand that many close while others stay open despite a similar ability to follow public health precautions.” The plaintiffs are represented by Attorney Deborah Stevenson, a specialist in Constitutional law and a long-time advocate for personal liberty and limited government. “My clients simply want to hold their government representatives accountable to the oath they took to uphold and defend the Constitution and the laws of this state,” Stevenson said. “We have faith that the judges of our state court system, who also took that oath, will do the right thing, and declare any Executive Orders or rules that were implemented during this pandemic in violation of the Constitution and the laws of this state to be null and void, and to preclude the Defendants from acting unlawfully in the future.” https://www.ctbizfreedom.com/

June 15, 2020
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE

BUSINESS OWNERS, STATE SENATOR FILE LAWSUIT CHALLENGING
LAMONT’S ‘NON-ESSENTIAL BUSINESS’ DESIGNATION
 
Five small business owners and a sitting State Senator have filed a lawsuit challenging Governor Ned Lamont’s power to declare certain Connecticut businesses non-essential during the COVID-19 epidemic.

“The public health crisis has resulted in an alarming expansion of executive power in our state,” said Joe Markley, director of the Connecticut Business Freedom Legal Fund, which is sponsoring the lawsuit.  “It is essential that we define the limits of the governor’s power going forward, and we believe this lawsuit is the best way to settle the issue.”

Plaintiffs in the lawsuit are Melanie Rivera-Maurice, owner of Gelled by Mel; Brandon Rocco, of Fearless Fitness; Christina Marshall, of Roots an Organic Salon; Darin Reisler of Plus One Defense Systems; Chad Lockhart, of Hartford County Tattoo; and State Senator Rob Sampson, a Realtor from Wolcott.

“I recognize that Governor Lamont has had to make truly difficult decisions during this crisis,” Senator Sampson said.  “However, over time it has become clear he has shifted from addressing legitimate public health concerns to advancing a political policy agenda.  Many of his executive orders constitute overreaches of his authority which must be challenged.

“My neighbors are not subjects but American citizens, and they deserve to be treated as such.  I am proud to stand with fellow business owners who have suffered tremendously as a result of unfair and arbitrary decisions.   I’m confident the court will recognize that it is not within the governor’s power to determine which businesses are essential, and to demand that many close while others stay open despite a similar ability to follow public health precautions.”

The plaintiffs are represented by Attorney Deborah Stevenson, a specialist in Constitutional law and a long-time advocate for personal liberty and limited government.

“My clients simply want to hold their government representatives accountable to the oath they took to uphold and defend the Constitution and the laws of this state,” Stevenson said.  “We have faith that the judges of our state court system, who also took that oath, will do the right thing, and declare any Executive Orders or rules that were implemented during this pandemic in violation of the Constitution and the laws of this state to be null and void, and to preclude the Defendants from acting unlawfully in the future.”

https://www.ctbizfreedom.com/

column31: I am looking for direction for what type of action, if any, that I should take. column36:
Edit to add: Dawson was officially diagnosed with Autism Spectrum Disorder on Aug. 20th. And yes, we know about TRS and nemechek protocol. 

This is the hardest thing I’ve ever written... I may forget everything I want to say, and I may just ramble, but I’m looking for some light at the end of the tunnel. This is our story...

I have 3 sons, Nolan who will be 12 this winter and is from a previous relationship, Dawson who is 17 months and my second son but my husband’s first son, and Leonidas that is 5 1/2 months old, also with my husband. 

Dawson came after multiple losses. He was so loved before even being born, so anticipated, and such a blessing after so much heartache.  He was so silly, engaging, beautiful, full of life, speaking, and was hitting all other milestones like a champ prior to his 12 month vaccines.  Then came the vaccines and along came a change that I never in my life thought I’d have to experience. Like the flip of a switch, the boy we grew to know and love was gone. The light in our sons eyes went out, almost leaving an emptiness in his beautiful blue eyes that is heartbreaking everytime I think about it.  He stopped speaking, started OBSESSING over one particular show, started to become obsessed with things that had to do with hand sensory (dragging hands on carpet, grass, brushes, etc... over and over and over...) stopped wanting to make eye contact, no longer wanted to cuddle, stopped non-verbal communications like pointing and waving, stopped actually playing with toys and rather messes with certain objects in a way that comes off as OCD rituals, in my opinion, prefers to climb, spin, or run back and forth over and over, NEVER EVER EVER answers to his name, started to fall a lot, and does what we have found through research is called, “verbal and hand stimming”, the list goes on and on... (after we noticed this he did get ear tubes placed, we see a slight difference, but nothing super exciting...)

We made an appointment with the pediatrician, expressed our concerns, and were thankfully “heard” by her. She has referred us for autism testing, we quickly filled out and returned the paperwork from the behavioral specialist who will do an in person eval, and are also awaiting the state programs for in home assessment for things like speech therapy, etc... we 100% are prepared for a diagnosis of ASD. He just turned 17 months, but we could tell something happened and that he was “different” than before at 12 months. Has anyone had success with intense therapy? We know everyone’s outcome can vary, but need to hear stories of hope in our dark times. 

If you made it this far, thank you in advance! I’m including pics of my little guy, 1 before the vaccines, and 1 after.

column36:
Bill Gates says 'Final Hurdle' To Distributing a Covid-19 Vaccine Will be Convincing People to TAKE IT

June 26, 2020

Microsoft billionaire Bill Gates lamented the US is 'not even close' to doing enough to fight the pandemic, before warning that the vaccine he wants to inject into every human on the planet does require their consent first.

Speaking to Anderson Cooper at a CNN town hall on Thursday, Gates insisted the US was “experiencing a rebound” in Covid-19 infections even accounting for the increase in testing. That increase, the software tycoon reminded his interviewers, was accomplished by local governments in spite of - not because of - the White House.

Gates seemed miffed that Washington wasn’t following his instructions more closely, complaining that “it’s possible to ramp up testing for a new pathogen very, very fast” if they’d just do as they were told. He blamed the higher infection numbers in the US, which continues to lead the world with upwards of 2.5 million confirmed cases and over 125,000 deaths, on the nation’s failure to adopt the same measures as everyone else.

“Other countries” are “restraining their behavior,” imposing restrictive lockdowns and quarantines, and adopting comprehensive contact tracing, Gates hinted, sounding impatient with the US’ “very large case spread,” which he called “embarrassing.”

Some people almost feel like [Covid-19 is] a political thing, which is unfortunate.

“Even to inconvenience themselves with masks requires maybe someone they know to not only test positive but maybe get very sick as well,” he added.

Gates, who has repeatedly expressed a desire to inoculate the world’s population with whatever vaccine emerges from the research laboratories he is funding, admitted the shot might be rolled out before it’s working perfectly. “It’s possible the vaccine will be better at protecting you individually and not stop you from transmitting…it’s not guaranteed that the vaccine will be a perfect transmission blocker.”

Boasting that “the logistics in the US are not an issue at all,” Gates bragged that “we can get this thing out there” before acknowledging that “you’ll have a ‘choice’ whether you take the vaccine or not, so there’s that final hurdle.”

The billionaire seemed unconcerned by the “vaccine hesitancy” factor, however, even though over a third of Americans have professed some concern over the safety of a coronavirus vaccine, citing the politicization of the issue, the rushed timetable, the less-than-stellar reputation of some of the individuals involved, and other issues.

Some 70 to 80 percent of the world’s population will have to take the vaccine before anyone can hope to live a normal life again “with people taking vacations,” travel, and sporting events, Gates explained, implying they had no choice.

column35: Dr. Andrea Nazarenko, PhD
column36:
Would you feed your infant diet soda?

Of course not!

Yet, the incidences of pregnant women drinking diet sodas and other foods with sugar alternatives is increasing at a drastic rate. 

(Roughly 5% of pregnant woman drink it on a daily basis! 😯)

Many moms believe that sugar alternatives will help reduce the risk of obesity in themselves and their babies. 

Unfortunately, the opposite is true. 

Sugar alternatives can cross the placental barrier, impacting the health of the developing fetus... altering their microbiome.

This exposure matters.  

When moms consumed artificially sweetened beverages (like diet soda) during pregnancy, infants were more than twice as likely to be overweight at 1 year of age. 

Exposure to artificial sweeteners is linked to a high infant BMI at 1 year of age. 

Prenatal exposure can result in a preference for sweet foods later in life - all the way into adulthood. This sweet preference can establish a foundation of unhealthy food choices throughout life. 

Interestingly, the associations between maternal consumption and child's weight was not seen in the consumption of sugar-containing beverage counterparts. 

Moral of the story?  DRINK MORE WATER. 💧🥤💦

Communications@doe.state.nj.us

https://www.facebook.com/njdeptofed

Phone: 609-376-3500

Talking points for emails to NJDOE, local BOEs, Office of Licensing

Add your own thoughts or use some bullet point listed below.

I am writing to you in regards to the possibility of New Jersey requiring all children and teachers to wear masks throughout the entire school day. Actions to protect our children and staff in schools should be decided on with sound science, while considering social and emotional repercussions. 

I do not want to see anyone harmed further by the misguided directives of decisions based on fear rather than facts. Mask do not prevent the spread of COVID-19. At best, masks prevent droplet from a cough, at worst masks cause a vast array of physical and emotional health disorders. Emotional trauma is irreversible and I will not support my child being subjected to this type of thoughtless, forceful, and misguided social experiment.

Mask concerns:

🌟 Expecting children to wear masks throughout the entire school day is not healthy or reasonable

🌟 Doctors have expressed safety and health concerns for prolonged mask wearing (links below)

🌟 There is no mask approved by the FDA for use by children

🌟 There is ZERO scientific evidence that masks lower the spread of Covid-19

🌟 There are no safety studies proving prolonged mask use by children is safe.

🌟 We must determine the best choices through logic not through fear (many mask product packaging now say they do NOT prevent the spread of Covid-19)

🌟 ”The clinical research on this topic is clear: even when handled and worn properly, which is definitely NOT happening in the public spaces, wearing a mask in public offers little or no protection from infection. “ Dr. Meehan

🌟 School is already an obstacle for many students with special needs, we don’t need to traumatize our students.

🌟 The trauma is already being discussed by the schools in an attempt to lower the effects, but there is no way to prevent this and the damage will be permanent.

Suggested Actions to Protect Staff and Students:

🌟 Staff and students stay home when sick, are sent home if become sick in school

🌟 Effective hand washing techniques should be taught and utilized as often as possible

🌟 As with other school  habits, students can “catch/cover their cough”  as we have taught for years in school.

🌟 Discuss more common serious health concerns like Strep throat and how the above suggestions can help mitigate that and many common health concerns.

I believe the principles talked about in this excellent video on Founder John Dickinson, known as the "Penman of the Revolution, wrote Letters From a Farmer in Pennsylvania during the time leading up to the Revolution, which was very important in uniting the 13 Colonies. Here's a few quotes: "Although the 'Farmer' necessarily focused on taxes, he addressed other political questions as well. One was how a free people should respond to government usurpation. "However, opposition should proceed cautiously...citizens must first petition for redress of grievances. Only if petitioning was unsuccessful should citizens proceed to peaceful civil disobedience. Only if both those steps failed, should they employ force. In a document he and Thomas Jefferson wrote together, The Declaration of Causes and Necessity for Taking up Arms, they say, "...the arms we have been compelled by our enemies to assume, we will, with unfailing perseverance, employ for the preservation of our liberties; being with our [one] mind resolve to dye Free-men rather than live slaves. Start doing your job parents

Your job is to be as informed as possible about everything that pertains to your child's life. Nothing is more important than their health. Your duty is to educated yourself instead of blinding trusting what you've been told.

Parents make decisions...not doctors. Unfortunately parents aren't doing their job and give in to false fear and mental programming where they outsource the parental decisions to some wearing a white lab coat who really has no clue at all about what's really going on.

It's not hard to learn about vaccines at all. You don't need a fancy degree. You don't need initials in front of your name. You don't need to sport a white lab coat. You just need to try. You have to want to learn. You have to want to start thinking instead of repeating. Put down that drink. Put down that t.v. remote. Pick up that vaccine insert. Start reading those studies. Start listening to those speaking out.

I'm done with those parents who are just going along. This is your damn wake up call. Your coward mentality isn't flying anymore. This is about saving the children from a future that involves becoming yet another statistic because you as a parent were too damn lazy and scared to think and act for yourself and do what's best for the children. If that makes you uncomfortable that's too damn bad. This is bigger than you. The children are counting on each of us and I'm tired of watching some parents be let off the hook because they refused to learn what they were easily capable of learning.

You don't get a free pass anymore. You don't get to say you didn't know vaccines were dangerous. You don't get to say you didn't know they can kill and cause neurological damage. There are millions of us sounding the alarm on this issue. Your inability to think and act isn't good enough. If you are opting in to the poisoning of children and I find out your going to hear about it from me....I will be a deafening voice you won't be able to shake or hide from. 

Starting right now....

Decide if you want to learn the easy way or the hard way. Decide what the future looks like for your children. Start thinking of what you're going to say to them when they ask what you were doing instead of learning about these shots. Start coming up a way to explain why you failed to act to save them when there was overwhelming evidence of the dangers of vaccines. No more free passes parents. Start putting in the work. It's time to wake up.

Folks, this needs to be shared far and wide. Here is the proof that the increased coronavirus cases are due to testing and not to a huge second outbreak of SARS-CoV-2 in the country. The proof: ***The Case Fatality Rate (CFR) has DROPPED ALMOST 9% in the last two weeks in the United States.*** The CFR is calculated by taking confirmed COVID deaths and dividing it by confirmed COVID cases. The more testing you have, the more confirmed cases you get, and the lower the CFR. Here are the numbers: June 9th Confirmed COVID cases: 2,011,548 Confirmed COVID deaths: 113,254 CFR: 5.63% June 24th Confirmed COVID cases: 2,391,336 Confirmed COVID deaths: 122,985 CFR: 5.14% A drop from 5.63% to 5.14% represents a decrease of 8.7%. SARS-CoV-2 has not gotten less deadly in the last two weeks. The only thing that can reduce the CFR by almost 9% in 15 days is increased testing. That is where your "huge outbreaks" are coming from: more tests. The media and certain politicians should be ashamed for what they're doing. People have lives and families they need to be focused on. It is immoral and disgraceful to be scaring Americans with these false doomsday proclamations.

column35: Fight for Equal Rights: Oppose Bill 49 and 11
column36:
Please bring your family and musical instruments to the legislature lawn where we will be united in music to bring about awareness and change in our community. 

This will be our fourth event in opposition to Bill 11. All along we have said this is not a vaccine issue- it is a RIGHTS based issue. Our history is marked with policies made in circumstances where fear seemed to legitimize the use of power and control, and the trampling of individual rights and freedoms of particular groups.  We now look back on these policies in disbelief and shame.

Bill 11 started almost a year ago now, and now we see Bill 49. Bill 49 which would give government unlimited powers to make, break, or suspend our laws and regulations. A bill which would give the government power to stop, search and ask for documentation of its citizens. A bill which tramples rights, freedoms, and the bedrock of our democracy itself. Injustices and rights violations don't stop until we can understand that injustices and rights violations against one is an injustice and violation for us all.

What we choose today becomes part of our heritage. Let us choose unity, let us choose empathy, let us choose humanity. Or we risk repeating the same history to which we look back on in disbelief and shame. Harmful and discriminatory policies are not created by bad men and women, they are created when fear, insecurity and division is high. They are created because people, in this fear, insecurity and division fail to safe guard against this power and control. Mistaking the power and control for safety and security. 

We are all human, let us remember our mutual humanity and come together in unity to protect one another against divisive policies, against policies based on power, control, and fear. We are better than this New Brunswick. 


For more information On Bill's 11 and 49. Please see the links below. 

Bill 49:
https://www2.gnb.ca/content/gnb/en/corporate/promo/covid-19/news/news_release.2020.06.0338.html?fbclid=IwAR2wRpVb3_jMB1CoCqQng6yn3itCckd3z7fDoQlhTZKXc2I-byNjDxDC4CQ

https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/new-brunswick/emergency-powers-blaine-higgs-government-1.5607790?fbclid=IwAR0jYUXxyBn4q14jHzWYxt9XShtADMxy9koKZR89wEgv443Mm_4-u_KVS0o

Bill 11
https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/new-brunswick/emergency-powers-blaine-higgs-government-1.5607790?fbclid=IwAR0jYUXxyBn4q14jHzWYxt9XShtADMxy9koKZR89wEgv443Mm_4-u_KVS0o

Bill 11 would result in mandated medical interventions for children in the province to attend schools and daycares; this disproportionately impacts and discriminates against certain New Brunswickers, in particular, the French, the poor, those living in rural or Northern NB, and single parents. This is because accessing alternatives for public school and daycare services are either too costly, unavailable, unsupported, or inaccessible for these groups. 
The government assessed the legal implications of Bill 11 and was advised it would not stand up in a court of law, as it is unconstitutional. Rather than amend the Bill accordingly, the government employed the use of the notwithstanding clause for the first time in NB history. The purpose of the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms is to protect individual rights from being overridden by the needs of a majority. When used, the notwithstanding clause is meant to advance or further protect our rights and freedoms. The government has failed to demonstrate how it’s use in the case of Bill 11 meets this criteria, and has failed to demonstrate or justify the need for the notwithstanding clause to limit and violate individual rights and freedoms in this context. The use of the notwithstanding clause is an admission on the part of the government that Bill 11 is unconstitutional and infringes on our Charter of Rights and Freedoms- which are embedded in our constitution. Specifically, Bill 11 violates section 2, 7, and 15:
--Freedom of conscience and religion; 
--Life, liberty, and security of the person;
--Equality before and under the law and equal protection before   the law without discrimination.
Despite the impact to New Brunswickers, and the potential unprecedented infringement of rights, there has been no public consultation for Bill 11. An identical Bill, Bill 39, presented to the legislature in the summer of 2019, saw significant public opposition and was not explicitly supported by those in the medical community.

Quarantining healthy people is one big EXPERIMENT and the states that didn’t lock down had fewer deaths .. also the PCR tests are non specific and many false positives ...not surprised! All of this information must be strongly tempered by the nature of what is commonly called “the COVID19 test.” It has been assumed, almost with religious certainty, that this reverse transcriptase, polymerase chain reaction manufacturing technique is the only or best way to test for COVID19 infection. In fact, that technique was not designed for diagnostic purposes at all, and its designer, Dr. Kary Mullis, had specifically cautioned not to use it to diagnose infectious disease.[5] A further problem with the COVID19 test has been the assigning of an arbitrary number of iterations to produce a positive result. This has led to magnified errors with each iteration, such that the RT-PCR test applied to COVID19 has been found to have an 80% false positive rate, making it nearly useless for this application.[6] Despite these problems, “the COVID19 test” was adopted quickly in the US and around the world. Suspicion of test results have been rife since the beginning, famously highlighted when the President of Tanzania and Chemistry PhD John Magufuli submitted specimens from a goat and a piece of fruit, each submitted for testing with human names. Both samples were then declared positive for COVID19 infection.[7] The proportion of COVID19 deaths to all deaths is lower on average in the states without lockdown, the control group, than in the states with lockdown, the experimental group. This held true also in states with the same population density. Also, the percent of expected deaths, for the COVID19 period compared to previous years of the same season, from all causes, is as of this time lower in the free states than in the lockdown states after about two months of lockdown. Quarantine of an entire state population, for disease control purpose, is an experiment without historical precedent. The stated goal of quarantine of the well population was purportedly to reduce mortality from COVID19. CDC data proved the experiment failed. Both COVID19 death rates were lower, and overall deaths were lower than expected in the free states than in neighboring lockdown states. Further damage from society-wide quarantine, commonly known as martial law, is economic devastation from loss of employment and loss of small and medium-sized businesses. The collateral damage of suicides, alcoholism and other substance abuse, anxiety and depression from this debacle are not yet measured, nor yet measurable in full. Therefore, having failed in its stated goal, and having caused widespread violations of civil liberties and human rights, as well as economic and social havoc and widespread suffering, universal quarantine against infectious disease should not ever be repeated. column36:
TAKE YOUR MASK OFF!!  THE RISKS OUTWEIGH THE BENEFITS. 

Angela McGiver Willis' story about her daughter, Holleigh....👇👇

I got a call from my 26 year old daughter, Holleigh, who is a shift lead for Walgreen's, saying she didn't feel well and was having trouble breathing. She went to her doctor's office and was SHOCKED to find out that she had a COLLAPSED RIGHT LUNG!
He sent her straight to the ER! I was in complete SHOCK as well! 

My daughter was crying on the phone and could hardly breathe as she was driving herself to the ER... I got her calmed down, despite the fact that I was freaking!  We got to the hospital and of course my husband, our two sons and I couldn't go in. They put her on oxygen for two days in the hospital to see if her lung would recover, but it did NOT! Next, they put a chest tube in her! Everytime we tried to find out ANY information, they would NOT give us any! Our daughter was soooo medicated she didn't know what was happening! I was ALARMED! 

I contacted my attorney and got a Medical Power of Attorney and I walked into that hospital like I owned the place and went directly to her room. Keep in mind she had been there 2 1/2 days by herself, without any family knowing WHAT the heck was going on and WHY the heck this happened and WHAT caused her lung to just collapse. 

When I walked in, my daughter was sitting by herself, in the dark, in horrible pain because they had just put the chest tube in 6 hours earlier, and still had NOT given her any pain medicine. They brought her food and put on the tray table, but it was out of her reach, the tray table's wheels were broken, her blinds were closed, lights off, NO TV and BOTH trash cans were full! 

She was sobbing and when I opened her door and she saw me, she reached out for me with her good arm, sobbing harder. I ran to her and we cried and just hugged. Needless to say, my daughter had pneumothorax aka a collapsed lung, which CAN be fatal! WHY you ask? It was her CONSTANT USE OF HER FACE MASK! She wore her mask everyday for up to 9 hours a day at WORK and was extremely busy and breathing hard in her mask from over exerting herself. 

We breathe IN OXYGEN, we breathe OUT CARBON DIOXIDE. When exerting herself, she was NEEDED MORE OXYGEN, however, she was breathing in CARBON DIOXIDE which built up in her mask. She wasn't getting enough oxygen! As the CO2 increases, the lungs REFUSE IT, as a protective mechanism. When the lungs refuse it, it pushes the CO2 to the lining  (pleura) AROUND the OUTSIDE of the lung, and if it builds up with more CO2 outside the lung than the O2 inside the lung, it literally collapses! 

My daughter was in the hospital for one week with a chest tube and could have died, yet the CDC, doctors and scientists do NOT say anything about it! My daughter was perfectly healthy and a very hard worker and it still happened to her. Masks are NOT meant for HEALTHY people and they are definitely NOT for anyone who works hard or exerts themselves! I have researched this and have found other cases as well, yet NOBODY IS TALKING ABOUT IT! 

I respect people and I keep my distance, but after what I saw, I will NOT be wearing a mask again, unless I am sick and then, I will stay home! This is what grocery pickup is for. If Covid-19 was really so terrible, then the many doctors and nurses would NOT have taken their masks off in my daughter's room to talk to us or joke around with us.

A rather interesting feedback received from an NDP MP from British Columbia
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Dear Mr. Mitra,

Thank you very much for your e-mail in which you are seeking support for your e-petition.  Once your e-petition has been drafted and submitted to the House of Commons to be submitted onto the petition portal to be sponsored, our office will be notified of the sponsor request at which time, Mr. Cannings will review it prior to making his decision.

With that said, have you also considered sending this request to your MP also?

Again, thank you very much for writing.

Sincerely,

Jennifer Ratz, MA
To Richard Cannings, MP
South Okanagan-West Kootenay

________________________________

From: Tony Mitra <tonu@mac.com>
Date: June 23, 2020 at 2:44:19 AM EDT
To: Cannings, Richard - M.P. <Richard.Cannings@parl.gc.ca>
Subject: Please support my e-petition to the Parliament, for independent assessment threat of covid19 threat and response - corrected

To: Honourable ParliamentarianRichard Cannings, NDP, South Okanagan-West Kootenay, BC
Date: Monday, June 22, 2020
Subject: Who will support my e-petition to the Parliament, for independent assessment of covid19 and the damage done to Canada through this lockdown ?
[corrected]
Dear Member of Parliament Richard Cannings of BC

I write this letter seeking your support for an e-petition I want to create for the Canadian Parliament to consider ordering an independent, transparent, unbiased and verifiable assessment of
a) the real threat posed by this covid19
b) the scale of damage being inflicted on Canada, on the pretext of saving it from a flu.

I do believe these two demands are justified in the current extraordinary period in our lives. Any action of the government that greatly affects economy, freedom of choice and way of life for all Canadians should be assessed transparently and seriously first. The government has not undertaken any such independent in-house assessment that has been published to the citizenry, nor conducted any consultation with the people it represents.

I had tried once before to raise a similar e-petition on the government portal. However, all such e-petitions need a Parliamentarian to support. I had selected Ms Jody Wilson-Raybould, an independent MP from Vancouver, British Columbia to support it. To my misfortune, she did not respond to my appeal, and did not let me know that she was unwilling to support it. She just sat on it for one month, till the window for the e-petition to find a supporting MP expired. My effort thus failed.

So, this time, I am asking each and every politician in the Parliament, ahead of time to see if we have even a single MP that is willing to come out and support my e-petition that merely asks for the Parliament to conduct an independent analysis of how dangerous this covid19 really is, and how much damage to Canada has been and is being done to deal with it, and if the threat justifies the response. This letter goes to every parliamentarian. I am in search of one, just one, MP that will stand up for sanity and justice for thirty seven million Canadian citizens.

So, honourable parliamentarian Richard Cannings, are you willing to be the one to support my effort?

This will be a public letter to encourage other Canadians to also approach our politicians. So you may find it on YouTube, or BitChute, and also shared on social media. My name is Tony Mitra, everywhere.??Thanking you
Tony Mitra,

10891 Cherry Lane, Delta, BC, V4E3L7, Canada, (604)6497535, tony.mitra@gmail.com

column35: Ohio Advocates for Medical Freedom
column36:
☎️CALL to Action: Sub SB-1☎️

June 23rd and 24th are the FINAL days of Senate session and the LAST opportunity for CONFERENCE COMMITTEE to meet, modify, and move Sub SB1 forward to vote! If we put enough pressure on, and committee meets and comes to an agreement, then the next step would be a call to action for the House of Representatives to meet for “Emergency Session” so we can get this bill PASSED during the summer!
Ohio can’t afford to wait until fall to #RestoreTheBalanceOfPower at the statehouse. 
We need ACTION NOW!

Please FLOOD the voicemails and emails of Senate President Obhof, Senator Schuring and House Speaker Larry Householder to:

“Convene Conference commitee and make the changes necessary to Sub SB1 to bring the house and senate into an agreement that moves this bill forward! Ohioans need the balance of power to be restored Now! We can’t wait till the fall. Conference committee must be called, so Ohio can get back on track!”

OAMF leadership spoke with some of the senate members to find out what it would take to get the senate to come to agreement on moving this bill forward. 
The suggestions included the following:

✔️ Limit statewide health emergency orders to 21 or 30 days to go before JACARR (instead of 14, to allow for a more reasonable amount of time to assess the emergency situation and then bring it before the assembly.) 

✔️Create a joint bill that makes health department order presentations to come before the entire assembly, instead of the 10 hand-selected JACARR committee members. 

✔️Remove the language that could allow individuals to SUE the state for opening up too soon after a health emergency. 

These suggestions are reasonable. 
There is NO reason that the house and senate can’t agree on this and MOVE FORWARD. 
TELL THEM SO when you call and email! 

CALL and Email TODAY, Mon., Tues., & Weds!!!

column31: Good evening everyone! It’s an honor to be part of your group. Some of you know I co-host a podcast that is dedicated to discussing the various issues that confront us in Connecticut and in our nation. Listen2This has dedicated much of its focus on the COVID issue and getting people back to work and businesses reopened. You can find prior episodes on You Tube. This isn’t a shameless plug as we do not sell ads and do not charge anything. We are doing this because we’re appalled at what has happened to all of us as a result of this horrific and completely disingenuous government overreach and we want to “spread the word” as the First Amendment intended us to do. This Saturday evening we are going to tape the show from 1000 Degrees, 2941 Main Street in Glastonbury. 1000 Degrees is a terrific casual pizza, wings, and more restaurant owned by a great young couple who have placed their entire life savings into this small business. The past three months have been a living hell for them and their young family. We are taking the show there so they can tell their story. We are hopeful that other local small business leaders as well as everyday citizens will join us to tell theirs as well. This is our opportunity to show a small business that we care well beyond our posts and replies in this group. It’s an opportunity to share good food and drink with some new friends who have encountered all of the same things that have brought us together. So please join us Saturday at 6:30 pm at 1000 Degrees. Hope to see you there to help support a small local business get back on their feet. If you are interested in being interviewed on the podcast, feel free to send me a private message. We would love to have you on the show!

column36:
Folks, this needs to be shared far and wide.  

Here is the proof that the increased coronavirus cases are due to testing and not to a huge second outbreak of SARS-CoV-2 in the country.  The proof:

***The Case Fatality Rate (CFR) has DROPPED ALMOST 9% in the last two weeks in the United States.***

The CFR is calculated by taking confirmed COVID deaths and dividing it by confirmed COVID cases.  The more testing you have, the more confirmed cases you get, and the lower the CFR.  Here are the numbers:

June 9th 
Confirmed COVID cases:  2,011,548 
Confirmed COVID deaths:  113,254 

CFR: 5.63%

June 24th 
Confirmed COVID cases:  2,391,336 
Confirmed COVID deaths:  122,985 

CFR:  5.14%

A drop from 5.63% to 5.14% represents a decrease of 8.7%.  

SARS-CoV-2 has not gotten less deadly in the last two weeks.  The only thing that can reduce the CFR by almost 9% in 15 days is increased testing.  That is where your "huge outbreaks" are coming from: more tests.

The media and certain politicians should be ashamed for what they're doing.  People have lives and families they need to be focused on.  It is immoral and disgraceful to be scaring Americans with these false doomsday proclamations.

column34: NJ RESTART AND RECOVERY PLAN FOR EDUCATION 2020 Parents: Lend your Voice NJ School Districts are charged with creating individualized plans for Fall 2020, volunteer to help!
column35: Innovative Parenting NJ
column36:
The New Jersey Restart and Recovery Plan for education was released today.  (The document outlining the plan is available to review below). 

The NJ Governor & the NJ Commissioner of Education reviewed some of the steps they are recommending for all districts in NJ. However, they are leaving it up to the individual NJ school districts to create their own path back for September 2020.

We must take a deep breath and recognize the huge task the Governor has just laid at the feet of each individual school district in NJ.

If they have not done so already, NJ is encouraging every school district to establish a Restart Committee to collaborate to create a plan for September. These plans need to be submitted to the state by August 2020 (school districts now have 30 days to submit their Fall plans to the State). This is a tremendous task placed on superintendents and boards of education. It would behoove us as parents to volunteer to help, to sit on these committees and offer our input, expertise and guidance to help plan the reopening of our school districts. A simple email to your Superintendent and to your local School Board of Education members empathizing with their current situation and offering your services is one action step to consider right now. If they have already formed a committee in your school district, find out who to contact to offer suggestions, links to articles, and opinions to and email those committee members. You may also consider writing a letter to the editor of your local Newspapers.

All of these plans will be created and updated in real-time and guidance may change. We, as parents, need to be patient with this process while also recognizing that this is an important opportunity activate in our communities, to get involved and build relationships with our local school board.

Link to the New Jersey Restart and Recovery Plan for Education: https://nj.gov/education/reopening/NJDOETheRoadBack.pdf?fbclid=IwAR0YGBH8y6ZHwFePvdsfb5ap7GbqH9ZzMVt96Mt2dLGVOZfevslBnSv8VzI 

Find your Superintendent’s email address here: https://homeroom5.doe.state.nj.us/directory/

Here are three articles to review that examine if children are the primary spreaders of COVID-19:

Children are not COVID-19 super spreaders: time to go back to school https://adc.bmj.com/content/105/7/618.long

Evidence summary of potential for children to contribute to transmission of SARS-CoV-2
https://www.hiqa.ie/sites/default/files/2020-05/Evidence-Summary_Covid-19_Spread-in-Children.pdf.pdf

Children unlikely to be the main drivers of the Covid-19 pandemic https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/apa.15371

column36:
To: Honourable Parliamentarian Mario Beaulieu, BQ, La Pointe-de-l'Île, QC
House of Commons, Ottawa, Ontario, Canada, K1A 0A6
Date: Monday, June 22, 2020
Subject: Who will support my e-petition to the Parliament, for independent assessment of covid19 and the damage done to Canada through this lockdown ?

Dear Member of Parliament Mario Beaulieu of QC,

I write this letter seeking your support for an e-petition I want to create for the Canadian Parliament to consider ordering an independent, transparent, unbiased and verifiable assessment of
a) the real threat posed by this covid19
b) the scale of damage being inflicted on Canada, on the pretext of saving it from a flu.

I do believe these two demands are justified in the current extraordinary period in our lives. Any action of the government that greatly affects economy, freedom of choice and way of life for all Canadians should be assessed transparently and seriously first. The government has not undertaken any such independent in-house assessment that has been published to the citizenry, nor conducted any consultation with the people it represents.

I had tried once before to raise a similar e-petition on the government portal. However, all such e-petitions need a Parliamentarian to support. I had selected Ms Jody Wilson-Raybould, an independent MP from Vancouver, British Columbia to support it. To my misfortune, she did not respond to my appeal, and did not let me know that she was unwilling to support it. She just sat on it for one month, till the window for the e-petition to find a supporting MP expired. My effort thus failed.

So, this time, I am asking each and every politician in the Parliament, ahead of time to see if we have even a single MP that is willing to come out and support my e-petition that merely asks for the Parliament to conduct an independent analysis of how dangerous this covid19 really is, and how much damage to Canada has been and is being done to deal with it, and if the threat justifies the response. This letter goes to every parliamentarian. I am in search of one, just one, MP that will stand up for sanity and justice for thirty seven million Canadian citizens.

So, honourable parliamentarian Mario Beaulieu, are you willing to be the one to support my effort?

This will be a public letter to encourage other Canadians to also approach our politicians. So you may find it on YouTube, or BitChute, and also shared on social media. My name is Tony Mitra, everywhere. Thanking you

Tony Mitra,
[address & contact details]

column35: Cindy
column36:
Status of COVID-19
As of 19 March 2020, COVID-19 is no longer considered to be a high consequence infectious disease (HCID) in the UK.

The 4 nations public health HCID group made an interim recommendation in January 2020 to classify COVID-19 as an HCID. This was based on consideration of the UK HCID criteria about the virus and the disease with information available during the early stages of the outbreak. Now that more is known about COVID-19, the public health bodies in the UK have reviewed the most up to date information about COVID-19 against the UK HCID criteria. They have determined that several features have now changed; in particular, more information is available about mortality rates (low overall), and there is now greater clinical awareness and a specific and sensitive laboratory test, the availability of which continues to increase.

The Advisory Committee on Dangerous Pathogens (ACDP) is also of the opinion that COVID-19 should no longer be classified as an HCID.

The need to have a national, coordinated response remains, but this is being met by the government’s COVID-19 response.

Cases of COVID-19 are no longer managed by HCID treatment centres only. All healthcare workers managing possible and confirmed cases should follow the updated national infection and prevention (IPC) guidance for COVID-19, which supersedes all previous IPC guidance for COVID-19. This guidance includes instructions about different personal protective equipment (PPE) ensembles that are appropriate for different clinical scenarios.

column35: Chantal
column36:
🤖🤖COMPLACENT & COMPLIANT🤖🤖

As we slowly come out of lockdown I am noticing that people are generally complacent with the “new normal” that MSM has told them they must comply with. This is greatly disturbing to me for various reasons.

As difficult and confusing as it was for 90% of the world to go in to lockdown, there were some amazing benefits for all of us that our governments had not expected. Firstly people got to STOP 🛑 for the first time in years. So many of us had been so caught up in the rat race and feeding on MSM and government lies that we had forgotten to use our most important tool. OUR MINDS. 

We starting interacting with our families more. Much more. We remembered how to LOVE again. It was like our blinkers were off and we could re-focus again. What initially started as fear for a virus, gave way to LOVE 💖 for one another. 

Then as we sat and spoke and occasionally looked up at our TV’s we noticed something strange happening. The narrative we always believed was unravelling before our eyes. It was like seeing “The Wizard of Oz” from behind the curtain for the first time. In great numbers we started to wake up and use OUR MINDS to think freely and research. We did it because we had time. We did it for our families. We did it for LOVE 💖.

What we saw unfolding baffled us and as a collective we sstarted to stand up. We saw the 5⃣G towers being put up around us and small cells on every block and said I DO NOT CONSENT to having this radiation in my environment and I DO NOT CONSENT to having all of my movements tracked. I WAS NOT INFORMED correctly about this new technology and I WON’T ALLOW it to go ahead without thorough testing.

We stood up to the corruption and lies in regards to mandatory vaccinations and microchips. We stood up to apps tracking our every movement. We stood up to becoming a cashless society due to a “virus” with a lower mortality than the flu. We MARCHED. We UNITED. We GREW WITH LOVE 💖. WE STOOD UP. 

My heart burst with pride on May 30th when across the world people of all races, religions and backgrounds collectively marched, knowing their rights to freedom and spoke eloquently and peacefully about a new, fair and just future for all. I had HOPE.

So I ask you all to do one thing for me as you come out of lockdown. Please don’t forget the lessons learnt through what felt like the toughest time of your life.

💛 WE DO HAVE THE RIGHT TO FREEDOM 💛

💛 WE DO HAVE THE RIGHT TO SAFE TECHNOLOGY 💛

💛 WE DO HAVE THE RIGHT TO BE CLOSE AGAIN 💛

💛 THE “NEW NORMAL” IS WHATEVER “WE” WANT IT TO BE💛

Please don’t ever go back to what you were before. 2020 is your year to stand up and take back your rights. We won’t stop until we have safe technology in regards to 5⃣G. Let’s do this. 💛

#IDONOTCONSENT
#YOUCHOOSEYOURNEWNORMAL

column36:
Because government has taken on the role of what type of mask you must wear and even in what direction one must walk, the role of government will next clearly expand to how to hang toilet paper (yes, that's highly contentious), how to wipe, how to floss, how to do one's laundry, how to clean one's home and how to fold one's socks.

If government is going to be so OCD, why has it NOT demanded all healthcare workers, nursing home employees and foodservice employees to: 

(1) wash their hands for 20 seconds before they even enter the room  with the food and the patient; then
(2) wash their hands for 20 seconds before they even leave the room with the food or the patient; then
(3) be fired immediately for not? 

That's actually far less arbitrary and restrictive than these wholeseale, indiscriminate attempts to reorder all society and life as we know it (and there's far more proven science behind it than the masks or the social dimwitting). 

Of course, Dr. Ignaz Semmelweis was a little too far ahead of his time in 1847. He would still be shouted down today by Governor Lamont, who would rather do all the wierd, insane and bizarre things he ordered and just plain isn't following himself.   

No, I am NOT suggesting this be an executive order. What I am suggesting (and science backs it up) that this all could have been over a lot sooner with that hands on approach.

The narrative describes how it is possible for the Lamont related businesses (under the Oak HC/FT umbrella) can realize totally tax free profit by using a Cayman Islands Fund with one Delaware corporation as its sole general partner.

Now if that all sounds tough to get your head around, kindly keep in mind that the funding for major Lamont (Oak) holdings such as Sema 4, (which gov. himself, copped to holding in Oak) and Ocrolus and Urjanet (tied into the CT Emergency Business Loan program) come directly from either local debtors,state prop funds, or through federal CARES ACT funding. 

So if the scheme we describe above is being used , "free money" gets put through a covert meat grinder to grow and show up as fully tax free profit down the road. 

In addition, we have NO IDEA what the state is paying Sema4 for Covid testing so we have no idea how much money is hypothetically being laundered into this part of the scheme. The "price" part is redacted from the contract for display, and no one (but us few) have asked any questions about this.

**Now do you think that is bad? It might just even be worse.**

**So this would be the ultimate power drive:** Use state retirement money to prop up Oak HC/FT portfolio companies, (many of whom may fail given start up business risks), while the Lamonts and Oak waltz several of their winners out the door to a tax-free profit. 

The retirees? 

Well, they will either have their pensions cut or will turn to taxpayers (read: you and me) for a bailout. 

(Wow, I can’t wait to break THAT news to some of our clients!)

Now no one seems to confront the gov with any of these really hard questions other than me and several others, but I explained to Lee Elci that if the gov and his aides were confronted, they would be pulling the “Fog of War” defense, which frankly, is a ton of horse manure. In closing, I said that even still, the gov. should be given the benefit of the doubt. Finally after disclosing all of the family mazes, including the relevance (or not) of no less than 20 "Oak HC/FTs" in Delaware, you can either resign (as I believe you should) or undo some of these horrible wrecks you have left us all with. column35: Bantam
column36:
Copied.. 
“Something you didn't know about "CASH". 

Alot of people don't see what's coming with how the government is pushing towards a cashless society. Especially with the ramp up of Covid-19. This should be worrying alot of you who understand commerce. We should be fighting for our right to use cash as a legal tender more often.

Why cashless society is the worst thing for us all.

Cash is the most liquid asset and can be used immediately to perform economic actions like buying, selling, or paying debt, and meeting immediate wants and needs. 

Once you have no hold of physical currency, the control of your invisible cash is in the hands of the banking institutions and government. Without cash, your control over your immediate assets becomes a digital illusion that can be controlled and manipulated as seen fit by the banks as well as the governments. 

The government and banks can reserve the right to hold on to, postpone or lock your available funds in case of pandemic, economical crash, civil war, protests, refusal to co-operate, tax, refusal to be vaccinated, even if the government or the banks are illegally operating. 

The idea of you having control over your money is just an illusion. The profiteers are the banks and by any means necessary, the banks will manipulate, bribe and pay off politicians to pass the law or regulation of the reduction of cash flow? Why?

Every physical penny that you hold in your pocket represents your control and your power of economic circulation, growth and exchange of goods. Once you are no longer in possession of physical currency, your bank is. 

The dream of every bank is to have full access, holdings and control of your money. This money becomes their borrowing and lending power. (E.g. 2009 US Bank Bail out. (Movie Big Short is about this crisis).

Banks charge you fees to safe hold your money. They also charge you transaction fees and withdrawal fees. Fees, fees, fees whilst they have your money and operate with it. Shouldn't it be the other way around?? 

Point is, if bank has your cash, the bank has control. I've noticed a huge reductions in cash handling for apparent reason of reducing the spread of covid-19. Really?? So it's ok for the sales assistant to handle your shopping goods, your groceries, pack your bags, pass you the bag and the receipt but it's not ok to handle your cash? Absolutely incredible bullshit. 

Use your cash, it's against the law for anyone to refuse the cash payment in exchange for goods and services. 
Take back the control of your life.”

column35: Mark Meuser
column36:
The numbers that prove just how bad of a governor Gavin Newsom is. 

According to the June 11th U.S. Department of Labor weekly job report, last year, the total new unemployment claims across the nation was 220,186. This week, California alone had 258,060 new claims.

According to the Census, California has 24,892,700 individuals between the age of 18-65. According to weekly job report, California has a total of 2,854,773 individuals on unemployment.

While California has a total of 2,854,773 people currently on unemployment which is 15% of the nation's current unemployment (18,919,804), California only has 12% of the nation's population (39,512,223 out of 328,239,523).

According to the CDC, California has 4,007 deaths "involving COVID-19" while the nation has 98,695. This means that California only has 4% of the nation's COVID deaths. (According to Gavin Newsom, the state of California has 5,063 total deaths which is a 26% increase from the official CDC reported numbers. I used the CDC number for consistency in comparison).

Thus, while California has 4% of the nation's Covid-19 deaths, it has 15% of the nation's unemployment.

Let's look at the California Covid-19 deaths.

According to Gavin Newsom, 78% of Covid-19 deaths are by those over the age of 65, 15.9% from those 50-64, and 6.1% from those 18-49. 

Using Gavin's higher death rate of 5,063, that means in California, 1,114 working age Californians have died while 2,854,773 are currently unemployed.

This means that 1 out of every 22,345 working age Californian has died because of Covid-19 while 1 out of every 9 working age Californian is unemployed.

Thus for every working age Californian who has died 2,563 have lost their job.

column35: Renee
column36:
Playtime is so beneficial to the development of our children. 

Benefits of play:
-Develops skills in all areas of development: cognitive, physical, communication, and social/emotional
-Play promotes healthy habits
-Play is a natural stress  reliever
-Decision making
-Spontaneity a and healthy risk-taking skills
-Play helps children develop mindfulness as well as feel safe and secure to try new ideas and experiment
-Learn how to respond to and stop bullying behavior
-Connect with others.
-many more benefits

Play dates aren't just for the kids, though. We ALL benefit from them...

Social elements are ingrained in our very being. They cannot be easily removed. We NEED social activities in order to thrive. This is what a society is- a social construct of individuals that learn, grow, and work with one another. Socities shape our identities. They benefit us. These benefits can be endless, from feelings of comfort to motivation to healthy behaviors to development of empathy to effective communication and so on and so forth. 

"Psychologist Susan Pinker states that direct person-to-person contact triggers parts of our nervous system that release a “cocktail” of neurotransmitters tasked with regulating our response to stress and anxiety.
In other words, when we communicate with people face-to-face, it could help to make us more resilient to stress factors in the long run."
-Medical News Today

Social interactions are GOOD for us in many ways. Social contact allows us to release oxytocin, making us more resilient to stress factors. Dopamine also plays a factor here. With delightful interactions, we release dopamine. It acts as a natural pain killer. It's the "happy" chemical we all need for good mental health. There is evidence that touch can actually relieve physical pain. Just by being around family and friends we build strength in character, body, mind, and spirit. Being with people just feels good....because it IS good.

There are many reasons play dates are good for ALL of us. Remember, fun and play isn't just about the kids. Adults also need these interactions in order to thrive, to live. After all, a society without interaction is just a collection of bodies.

column31: VEZINA: Constant training improves police performance | Toronto Sun, June 23, 2020 https://torontosun.com/opinion/columnists/vezina-constant-training-improves-police-performance Here’s an idea for better policing — enhanced training. We don’t need to wait on slow government investigations to start improving it. As an example, police could have 20% of their working days — one day a week — as a training day where they would run through scenario drills related to every facet of their job. Civilian volunteers would act in the role of “non-police” in these scenarios. A charity could co-ordinate the logistics. Officers would go through training scenarios with different levels of difficulty based on the compliance level of the civilian actors, and would thus have a safe environment to succeed, fail, and learn. After the exercises, the officers would discuss the experience with the civilian volunteers. They would work together to improve their understanding of the nuances of the situations they were involved in. The civilian actors would inform the officers: “When you did this, I felt scared/safe. Is there a way you can do that differently?” Officers would inform the civilians: “When I am in this situation, my rules/training/experience/etc. tells me to do ‘this.’ What would you prefer I did for us both to feel safe?” Police training should: — Ensure that the training is job-ratio based — Integrate civilians into the police training process — Create intuitive professional development feedback mechanisms — Provide an opportunity for civilians to normalize the “police experience” To understand the critical need for a significantly high percentage of a police officer’s job to be devoted to training, look at the difference between military special forces and police training. Both are put into dangerous situations that require complex and quick decisions. Police generally train for (depending on the service) three to nine months in a college, supplemented by small courses over time on specific issues. By comparison, special forces teams for U.S. Navy SEALs train 18 months for a six-month deployment. Police officers can graduate from their college, go for 20 years without any intensive training, never need to point or shoot their firearm, and then suddenly be thrust into a life-and-death situation with two decades of rust. In order to be effective, police need to practice complex decision-making scenarios regularly, as part of their weekly duties. Integrating civilians into these scenarios has numerous benefits. Police are thus exposed to people who can provide them with context about their communities, with their training constantly evolving intuitively, by design. Civilians are given a safe environment to behave how they genuinely would interact with a police officer during a traffic stop, a warrant execution, or when they are afraid for their lives. Feedback can then be immediately given to expand an officer’s experience and understanding of how best to do their job. Officer errors are identified in a controlled environment and immediately addressed. If necessary, officers can be taken off active duty to focus on re-training and professional development, before the error occurs in the field and a tragedy results. Constant training would also help to reveal officers under stress in their personal lives who may need to take time off work to decompress. Better to find out in a training scenario, than with live ammunition. To be sure, this won’t solve everything. There will still be issues with encounters between police and civilians. But constant training with civilian actors will directly address many of the controversies about police actions today and have additional benefits beyond the value of the training alone. When you have suggestions that benefit all parties, you don’t wait for a bureaucracy to bury it, or the news cycle to forget about the issue. You just go and do it. — Vezina is the CEO of Prepared Canada Corp. and has a graduate degree in Disaster and Emergency Management

Take Leprosy for instance.

The reason you don't fear leprosy is that there isn't a vaccine for it.

Wondering how many parents walk around daily concerned about their child contracting leprosy? It still exists- by the thousands in various parts of the world. The United States has roughly 200 cases every year. Did you know that? I didn't until I just looked it up.

Because there's no vaccine for leprosy.

You are afraid of what we vaccinate for because these illnesses are hyped up all of the time. It's propaganda. You are told what to fear, so they can then sell you an alleged solution.

Measles and others is a concern for you because you are told that it should be. But you don't walk around fearing leprosy. 
Your children haven't contracted it either.
Funny how that all works, isn't it?

The only diseases we fear are the ones that a vaccine has been developed and marketed for. We never feared measles and mumps in the early 20th century... Because the media didn't tell us to. #QuestionEverything #StayWoke #VaccinesDidntSaveUs."

column31: A major study released by a large group of scientists in Europe found genetic variations to be correlated to COVID-19 disease severity. The scientists compared the genomes of 1,980 patients with severe COVID-19 disease showing respiratory failure at hospitals in Italy and Spain to healthy controls or COVID-19 patients with mild or no symptoms [1]. The results of their genomewide association study analyzing 8,582,968 single-nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) identified two SNPs rs11385942 at locus 3p21.31, and rs657152 at locus 9q34.2 with significant implications in the pathogenesis of COVID-19. Locus 3p21.31 is associated with the SLC6A20 gene, which codes for a sodium chloride dependent transporter that mediates calcium-dependent uptake of imino acids and is involved in the transport of glycine [2]. Locus 9q34.2.coincides with the ABO blood group. In the patients examined, a blood-group-specific analysis showed a higher risk in blood group A, while blood group O seemed to confer a protective effect. Locus 9q34.2 is extremely important for the development of abnormal blood clots, thrombotic microangiopathy (TMA) that can lead to thrombosis and myocardial injury in severe COVID-19 infections. Locus 9q34.2 is where the protein ADAMTS13 (ADAM metallopeptidase with thrombospondin type 1 motif 13) is coded [3]. The ADAMTS13 protein cleaves the von Willebrand Factor (vWF). Defects in the ADAMTS13 gene are associated with thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura (TTP), a blood disorder characterized by thrombotic microangiopathy, and low platelet count. TTP is often seen together with atypical hemolytic uremic syndrome (aHUS), which is a major thrombotic microangiopathy (TMA) characterized by hemolysis [4]. ADAMTS13 is critical in the prevention of thrombosis because it cleaves the von Willebrand factor (vWF). Deficiency in vWF results in thrombus formation [5]. This is also the reason why ABO SNPs including rs657152 are associated with cardiovascular diseases [6]. ADAMTS13 is located downstream of CD147, a transmembrane glycoprotein, and therefore, can be negatively affected by CD147 modulation. SARS-CoV-2 spike protein has been found to bind to CD147 [7]. The binding to CD147 receptors has extremely far-reaching implications for the pathogenesis of COVID-19. My peer-reviewed paper discusses in-depth, how CD147 binding causes systemic damage during COVID-19 infection. “Loh, D. 2020. The potential of melatonin in the prevention and attenuation of oxidative hemolysis and myocardial injury from cd147 SARS-CoV-2 spike protein receptor binding. Melatonin Research. 3, 3 (Jun. 2020), 380-416. DOI:https://doi.org/https://doi.org/10.32794/mr11250069.” https://www.melatonin-research.net/index.php/MR/article/view/86/568 Have you had your AA and MEL today? References: [1] Genomewide Association Study of Severe Covid-19 with Respiratory Failure https://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa2020283 [2] https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q9NP91 [3] https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gtr/genes/11093/ [4] https://www.hematologyandoncology.net/files/2013/02/ho1012_sup171.pdf [5] https://www.ahajournals.org/doi/10.1161/STROKEAHA.116.015677 [6] https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3485501/ [7] https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.03.14.988345v1 https://edition.cnn.com/2020/06/17/health/coronavirus-genes-blood-type-study/index.html References: https://edition.cnn.com/2020/06/17/health/coronavirus-genes-blood-type-study/index.html

column36:
On August 29, 2019, ICWA Board members Bernadette Pajer and Drella Stein attended a presentation by KUOW's Isolde Raftery at the UW Bookstore on the topic of vaccination. In this five minute excerpt, Ms. Raftery presents a nonsensical theory about vaccination and racism that shocked us. Her remarks insult white women (like herself), and even worse, are discriminatory against people of color, implying that parents of color don't have the intelligence or research and observational skills to understand how and when their children are being harmed by a pharmaceutical product.

At the time, the ICWA board was deeply concerned we were witnessing the birth of a new social-marketing campaign by the drug industry -- labelling vaccination as an "anti-racist" act. History has shown us that the opposite is true. And now, we are beginning to see this campaign increasingly saturate the media. Drug companies and the government have a history of using and abusing communities of color to serve their own agendas. They are doing so again in this Covid Chaos. Rather than addressing the specific health needs of specific populations, such as deficient Vitamin D levels, they are building pressure to get rushed and dangerous vaccines to people of color -- first. We must all stand together to say no to rushed, untested vaccines. We must all stand together to protect those targeted to receive them. Nobody of any race, ethnicity, age, or occupation should be targeted as test subjects for the drug industry.

The entire 2019 presentation contained biased misinformation. Vaccines are liability-free for-profit products, mandated and promoted by the government. Without a fair and ethical press covering the subject, individuals are increasingly being stripped of medical, personal, and religious freedoms. To see the full presentation with slides pointing out some (but not all) of the misinformation, see the video on our youtube channel: https://youtu.be/5aKvsWAPw4U

column31: # Effects and risk’s do to prolonged usage of non-regulated face Mask. **Lack of Oxygen; Causes Cortisol. ** Stalls the body’s Immune system. Think of cortisol as nature’s built-in alarm system. It’s your body’s main stress hormone. It works with certain parts of your brain to ***control your mood, motivation, and fear***. Your adrenal glands -- triangle-shaped organs at the top of your kidneys -- make cortisol. It’s best known for helping fuel your body’s “fight-or-flight” instinct in a crisis, but cortisol plays an important role in a number of things your body does. How Does It Work? Your hypothalamus and pituitary gland -- both located in your brain -- can sense if your blood contains the right level of cortisol. If the level is too low, your brain adjusts the number of hormones it makes. Your adrenal glands pick up on these signals. Then, they fine-tune the amount of cortisol they release. Cortisol receptors -- which are in most cells in your body -- receive and use the hormone in different ways. Your needs will differ from day to day. For instance, when your body is on high alert, cortisol can alter or shut down functions that get in the way. These might include your digestive or reproductive systems, your immune system, or even your growth processes.

column31: A LETTER FROM A ZERO-REVENUE SMALL BUSINESS OWNER
column35: This is a re-share of a post
column36:
A lot of small business owners have asked me about the BCAP program that is being managed by BDC and EDC.

A lot of small business owners have asked why NO small businesses have been able to access the money.  After meeting with bank employees on the grounds anonymity, here is the letter I sent to the Chair of the Finance Committee.

Chair Easter,

Thank you for asking me to put forward commentary on the practices of the Business Development Bank of Canada (BDC) during my testimony before the Finance Committee on Tuesday, June 2, 2020.  I believe that the Federal government structured financing in a good faith through the BDC however, the organization is choosing to do things their way which is subsequently hurting all small businesses and not being used the way it was intended.

I have information, on good authority, that the major banks are not participating in the program. They are not even suggesting to their small business clients to access funding through the co-lending program established by the Federal government for several reasons. All the reasons are more alarming than the next. 

Firstly, I have been told by the big banks that their employees are not given "credit" for processing the co-lending program which takes eight to fifteen hours per client so their employees are not willing to mention the program to their clients. How is it possible that bank staff are more concerned about hitting their sales goals than the crisis their clients are in. This is unacceptable.  

Secondly, the major financial institutions go through an adjudication process with the small business. The bank goes through the process, adjudicates and then approves then funds. Once that process is completed, the way the co-lending program is SUPPOSED to work is the BDC reviews it.  

The Business Development Bank of Canada is supposed to confirm the business is eligible based on government criteria but forward. The Business Development Bank Of Canada then is supposed to refund the small businesses' principal lender.  What is happening is BDC assigns the file to one of their account managers and adjudicates it based on their criteria.  The BDC then let the bank know if the small business meets the eligibility requirements. 

As it stands today, the big banks do not want to get stung because if BDC says no, that the small business does not meet their criteria, the big banks are already on the hook.  The stalemate between the big banks and BDC have put small business further into crisis. This is unacceptable.

While BDC is supposed to cover the eighty percent of the loan and the big banks twenty, the small business owner must still guarantee it.  Because the banks are not pushing it, small businesses are having to go through the traditional routes of applying for loans through the Business Development Bank of Canada which comes with not only high-interest rates but personal guarantees. 

As taken, directly from my testimony June 2, 2020, "We need regulation or legislation that will prevent lending institutions from pursuing personal guarantees."  Mr. Easter, you asked whether this has all happened pre-liquidity or post, and I can tell you without a doubt this has happened post liquidity.  I can also confirm through my source that less co-lending applications have been approved and funded by the BDC than you can count on one hand nationally. 

We not only need government legislation that will prevent this during the pandemic also require personal guarantee protection on loans and leases that were signed pre-COVID as the complete shut down of business was of no fault of the great entrepreneurs of this country.

column36:
"June 8, 2020; U.S. Attorney's Office, District of Connecticut. Police officials, U.S. States attorneys, DOJ and FBI, DPH etc., announced that a Wallingford doctor was arrested for selling Opioid prescriptions for cash. He was charged with federal controlled substances and health care offenses related to the illegal distribution of prescription medication." This is but one example, out of so many, of Healthcare frauds and abuse in our State.

Fraud, abuse and waste in Medicare and Medicaid costs states billions of dollars every year, diverting funds that could otherwise be used for legitimate health care services. Not only do fraudulent and abusive practices increase the cost of Medicaid without adding value – they increase risk and potential harm to patients who are exposed to frivolous or unnecessary procedures. In 2015, improper payments alone totaled more than $29 billion, $52Billion in 2017, according to the U.S. GAO. 

"When a provider treats a Medicare or Medicaid patient, the provider must tell Medicare/Medicaid what services were provided so that the insurer can appropriately reimburse the doctor. Unethical providers may tell Medicare they provided a more expensive service than they actually did, which results in the provider receiving more money from Medicare than they should." This form of healthcare fraud is known as “upcoding” and is a violation of the federal False Claims Act. Upcoding is a serious problem at our State-run healthcare facilities. Medicare fraud and abuse is rampant in Connecticut. Not only is it costing us millions, it's costing us lives.

My kids would swing all day if I let them lol. They also like to climb up the slides. I let them as long as no one is trying to slide down. It's really good for large motor/muscle development. The swinging calms them. They'd fall asleep if they didn't have to hold on lol. 

When I was really young, I loved the merry-go-round. As I got older, it was swinging. As I got even older, I loved to play flag or touch football, baseball, kick ball, soccer, tennis, or even just tag. I loved to run. I also loved to go hiking around the little creeks and wooded areas that surrounded the parks I grew up near.

So, tell me, what do you and your kids like to do?
