column31: But the pandemic experience has brought on a surprising effect on this expected death rate among children. Starting in early March, expected deaths began a sharp decline, from an expected level of around 700 deaths per week to well under 500 by mid‐April and throughout May. [1] As untimely deaths spiked among the elderly in Manhattan nursing homes and in similar settings all over the country, something mysterious was saving the lives of children. As springtime in America came along with massive disruptions in family life amid near universal lockdowns, roughly 30% fewer children died. Was this a protective effect of school closures? Were teenagers getting themselves into risky situations at a lower rate? No. There was very little effect among school age children or adolescents. [3] Virtually the entire change came from infants. Somehow, the changing pattern of American life during the lockdowns has been saving the lives of hundreds of infants, over 200 per week. Deaths in infants and children occur at a higher rate in minority groups. [4] So the reduction in childhood deaths during the lockdowns has meant that the lives of black and Hispanic infants and children have been saved at a higher rate. https://childrenshealthdefense.org/news/lessons-from-the-lockdown-why-are-so-many-fewer-children-dying/ https://childrenshealthdefense.org/news/lessons-from-the-lockdown-why-are-so-many-fewer-children-dying/

column31: By Jon Rappoport As my readers know, I’ve been reporting on new types of technology that could be used in a coming COVID-19 vaccine—and warning about the consequences. One such technology is: DNA vaccines. They would alter recipients’ genetic makeup permanently. But Reuters has seen fit to claim: “A future COVID-19 [DNA] vaccine will not genetically modify humans.” This comes from their “fact-check team” — May 18, 2020: “False claim: A COVID-19 vaccine will genetically modify humans.” To reach this conclusion, Reuters cites two people: “Mark Lynas, a visiting fellow at Cornell University’s Alliance for Science group”, and “Dr. Paul McCray, Professor of Pediatrics, Microbiology, and Internal Medicine at the University of Iowa.” I have cited the New York Times, March 10, 2015, “Protection Without a Vaccine.” Here are quotes from the Times article: “By delivering synthetic genes into the muscles of the [experimental] monkeys, the scientists are essentially re-engineering the animals to resist disease.” “’The sky’s the limit,’ said Michael Farzan, an immunologist at Scripps and lead author of the new study.” “The first human trial based on this strategy — called immunoprophylaxis by gene transfer, or I.G.T. — is underway, and several new ones are planned.” [That was five years ago.] “I.G.T. is altogether different from traditional vaccination. It is instead a form of gene therapy. Scientists isolate the genes that produce powerful antibodies against certain diseases and then synthesize artificial versions. The genes are placed into viruses and injected into human tissue, usually muscle.” [Here is the punch line] “The viruses invade human cells with their DNA payloads, and the synthetic gene is incorporated into the recipient’s own DNA. If all goes well, the new genes instruct the cells to begin manufacturing powerful antibodies.” The Times article taps Dr. David Baltimore for an opinion: “Still, Dr. Baltimore says that he envisions that some people might be leery of a vaccination strategy that means altering their own DNA, even if it prevents a potentially fatal disease.” So it’s a battle of the experts. The two men Reuters cited, versus the Times’ David Baltimore. I don’t hold up the scientific work of any of these men for great acclaim. I’m only interested in which man knows whether a DNA vaccine would permanently alter the genetic makeup of every recipient’s DNA. David Baltimore is a Nobel Laureate (1975, in Physiology/Medicine), and the past president of the American Association for the Advancement of Science (1997-2006). He’s one of the most famous scientists in the world. I’m betting Reuters would happily trade their unknown experts for Baltimore, if he would side with their claim. Perhaps they’ll now approach him, and perhaps he’ll change his mind. But the NY Times has him on the record, in 2015, admitting that DNA vaccines do alter genetic makeup. World famous mainstream experts don’t readily admit this sort of thing out in the open, unless they’re stating the obvious. The verdict on the Reuters fact-check team? Fact-checkers checked the wrong box. Final point for the moment: Researchers are fond of saying their genetic technologies are quite safe. This a bald-faced lie. Claiming, for example, that a DNA COVID vaccine would alter humans’ genetic makeup in entirely predictable and harmless ways is like saying a car without brakes, doing a hundred miles an hour, set loose on a highway during rush hour, would create no damage whatsoever.

column31: I offer a reassuring graph and analysis that I hope will reduce fear. Living in fear is no way to pursue happiness!
column35: Tom
column36:
I keep a spreadsheet tracking the daily deaths in Texas that are reported on the Texas Department of State Health Services website.   I graph a 7-day rolling average to get a better perspective on what is going on because it is clear that weekend reports always drop and Monday reports spike.  The 7 day average gives a better directional indicator.

I freely admit that deaths are a lagging indicator, and I know there that media is reporting increased positive cases reported and increased hospitalizations which could result in increased deaths later, but I thought people might be interested in the perspective. this graph gives.

I am also not expecting deaths to go up much from whatever reporting of positive cases or hospitalizations are occurring.  I base that on a number of suspicions:

*  More testing will discover more cases.  My impression is that testing keeps ramping up.
*  I have seen several articles that say that asymptomatic cases are running at 70 to 80% of the identified positives.
*  I suspect that measures to protect the elderly and those with compromised immune systems are doing a pretty good job of stopping the spread with those vulnerable populations, and suspect (but do not know) that the bulk of the new cases are not in vulnerable populations, but in younger and those with more robust immune systems than we saw in the early phases of the disease.
*  I am hearing positive results from plasma treatment and hydroxyquinoline/zinc treatments.  As time goes by, I suspect that even those whose systems succumb to the disease more than most are getting treatments that increase chances of survival.  And I think the word is getting out that putting people on ventilators is not a likely workable way to stop death with COVID-19.
*  I suspect that large numbers of people are learning that taking the right supplements like 50 mg zinc, and big doses of vitamins D, and C and the others to boost the immune system will help withstand the worst of the disease if they catch it.  I have even heard one doctor suggest having tonic water (which has quinine, the cousin of hydroxyquinoline) on store as a immediate home remedy at the onset of COVID-19 symptoms.

I think that many people's expectations are that we can stop the spread of this disease.  I do not know how we can keep a functioning economy and allow people to earn a living and stop it.  We now know that COVID-19 is not a death sentence for all but a fraction of one percent of those who get it, primarily those with compromised immune systems including the elderly.  And those most at risk can protect themselves by sheltering in place, aggressively social distancing, and wearing of masks - the right masks like N-95.

I think the rest of us should expect to be exposed and have our immune systems do what they are designed to do - cope with it.  That is, after all, part of developing herd immunity.  The sooner we do it, the sooner we can get on with our lives.

I recognize that there are powerful forces who want to see us all buy their vaccine, and if we have gotten the disease and overcome it, their sales will be much less.  I do NOT want to dance to that Deep State tune.

So, I hope this graph and this discussion counteracts what I think is fear-mongering by those who lust to run our lives or be seen as caring about us.

This COVID-19 scare has given us each an opportunity to make sure that we are spiritually and mentally and emotionally prepared to face death and adversity.  Adversity and death, after all are part of the human condition.

Putting it another way, living in fear is no way to engage in the pursuit of happiness.

column36:
Shingles anyone 

Posted By: Vaxxter Staff 03/07/2017

The shingles vaccine is one of the most widely marketed vaccines on the market. It is difficult to turn on your  television in any capacity without enduring some celebrity endorsement over Zostavax. 

Approved in 2006, the vaccine uses a live virus, and it’s a big seller. But Merck’s manufactured goldmine also has a bit of a “murky” history in terms of side effects.

First, in 2015 the vaccine was found to cause cases of  chickenpox (the precursor to shingles). This led to a side effect being added to the label: Shingles. The vaccine targeting people looking to prevent or cure shingles was actually listing shingles as a potential side effect.

This past February, the situation worsened for Zostavax consumers as the FDA listed eye disorders to the list of side effects. Specifically listed was necrotizing retinitis and keratitis. This disorder causes scarring and inflammation of the eyes. It can lead to a loss of vision if left untreated.  

Researchers found that 20 cases of keratitis in both children and adults occurred within one month of taking the chickenpox of shingles vaccine. The researchers declared there was a likely relationship between the eye disorder and the vaccine but also stated that the research wasn’t intended to prove such. Instead, researchers put out this warning:

“While this is a rare occurrence, it’s important for physicians to know when giving the vaccine to individuals who have a history of the condition because it could be reactivated by the vaccine,” he said. 

This vaccine also contains monosodium glutamate, or MSG, as it is more popularly known as. The American Heart Association calls MSG  “common trigger for Atrial fibrillation.” It has also been linked to killing brain cells, obesity, Alzheimer’s, and Parkinson’s.

The shingles vaccine has the highest concentration of gelatin of any vaccine. Gelatin is a protein that can cause inflammation. There is a strong relationship between systemic allergic reactions, including anaphylaxis and injected gelatin. Allergic cross-reactions also occur to gelatin-containing foods.

More Shingles Vaccine Side Effects
Here is a list of side effects the manufacturer claims:

allergic reactions, which may be serious and may include difficulty in breathing or swallowing
chickenpox
fever
hives at the injection site
joint pain
muscle pain
nausea
rash
rash at the injection site
shingles
swollen glands near the injection site (that may last a few days to a few weeks)
Before taking any vaccine, know and understand the potential for side effects. Read the labels and do the research. Treat vaccines the same as any medicine you might be prescribed. The primary difference? If you have a reaction to a medication you can stop taking the pills. Have a reaction to a vaccine? You can’t un-vaccinate.

That is a load of nonsense.  What we want is elections that are honest and fair for everyone!  That requires a legitimate process that puts integrity at the top of the list of requirements.

There are tens of thousands of people on the voter rolls in Connecticut who should not be listed because they have moved, or passed on, or appear multiple times at multiple addresses.  This means that some addresses will receive multiple ballots for those that have lived there over the years.  Others won't receive their ballots at all - and this is just the beginning of the problems.

The largest one is that it is basically impossible to track and prosecute fraud.  If someone grabs all the ballots for an entire nursing home and completes and sends them, who will ever know?   

I am so saddened by what is happening in our country and this is just another terrible sign that we are headed the wrong way.  

Please consider sharing with your friends and neighbors why this is such a bad idea.  The existing absentee ballot law is still in effect.  You can still call and get yours.  I am all for that.  But sending millions of ballots by mail is not only expensive, it is an invitation for problems.

YOUR IDENTITY IDENTIFICATION TAKEN WITHOUT YOUR PERMISSION DURING THE REIGN OF LAMONT.

In living through a wild time with the pandemic, truthful reporting, self-dealing, riots, rigged systems, fake news written by biased college students, police defunding, protestors on highways and freeways, unexplained closures, forced and undeserved bankruptcies, (and other subjects too numerous to mention) taking place, I did not want to be remiss and not mention an absolute crime that occurred between our lovely state of CT and the "Boston Consulting Group" ("BCG") on May 9 of this year,  even though you may think it is pale by comparison.

Needless to say, most are familiar with the what took place. If you are not, the state signed a $2MM 15 page PHASE 1 "consulting services contract" where BCG is supposed to provide "expert guidance" on "Covid 19 Recovery".

Unfortunately, the contract is a whole lot more than that. 

In reading the same it is quite clear that the core of the deal involves "contact tracing" through the "BCG Key" Data Management system for every of the state's 3,500,000 residents. Of course no "mainstream" outlet has ever told you that contact tracing is a critical part of this agreement kids, (but its right there on Page 3).

Now, the "data" for the "Key" system and its contact tracing management is every bit of your personal identity information, transferred from you just as if an identity thief lifted it from you. I can't make it plainer than that.

Below, I have photoed and reproduced two (of maybe at least 15) shocking provisions in this PHASE 1 agreement) just to show that I am not just running off at the mouth. One picture deals with the lifted information, while the other is a "no publicity" provision.

If you are having difficulties reading each provision, I have copied them both, below.

First, the identity provision (on Page 6). This is what information BCS is intended to have on you and I.

*Confidential Information: Any name, number or other information that may be used, alone or in conjunction with any other information, to identify a specific individual including, but not limited to, such individual's name, date of birth, mother's maiden name, motor vehicle operator's license number, Social Security number, employee identification number, employer or taxpayer identification number, alien registration number, government passport number, health insurance identification number, demand deposit account number, savings account number, credit card number, debit card number or unique biometric data such as fingerprint, voice print, retina or iris image, or other unique physical representation. Without limiting the foregoing, Confidential Information shall also include any information that the State classifies as “confidential” or “restricted.” Confidential Information shall not include information that may be lawfully obtained from publicly available sources or from federal, state, or local government records which are lawfully made available to the general public.*

Next, the "no publicity" provision on Page 14.

*6.3 No Publicity. No Party will make any public announcement or press release regarding the Engagement or Services performed without the prior written consent of the other Party; provided, however, BCG has the right to refer to State as a client of BCG for promotional purposes with the written consent of the State. Except as required by law, neither BCG Deliverables nor reference to BCG may be included or made in any prospectus, proxy statement, offering memorandum or similar document or materials prepared for public distribution, except to the extent required by applicable law.*

Any WONDER why they wanted this to be a secret?

If you are not horrified at the above, politely please check your pulse.

Needless to say, the above is a horror. And its a federal crime per Secs . 6103 and 7216 of the Internal Revenue Code. States can only use a citizen's tax information for purposes of state income tax processing and no other purpose. As I explained on my segment of CBS 94.9 FMs' "Lee Elci Show" on June 16 as to how serious these code protections are supposed to be, even the Atty. General of NY State cannot get his own state to cough up state tax information on the President, so he moved a case through on very different grounds that has just been heard by the U.S. Supreme Court.

When I found this information out, I was (and am) livid. I've throttled my state representatives, and for days, the silence is deafening. Good news (if any) is that I have in from several sources that this development has been reported to the responsible Federal authorities. Its my contention that at the very least, every citizen should receive three years of state-paid (NOT state-run) identity theft protection for this really foul act.

"Opening Schools Safely in Orange County" Public Forum 

Location

Orange County Department of Education, 200 Kalmus Drive, Costa Mesa 

Start Time

6/24/2020 6:30 PM 

End Time

6/24/2020 9:30 PM 

Description

The Orange County Board of Education will discuss recommendations for reopening local schools during a public forum on Wednesday, June 24.

The forum, titled “Opening Schools Safely in Orange County,” is set to take place from 6:30 to 9:30 p.m. in the Board Room at the Orange County Department of Education, located at 200 Kalmus Drive in Costa Mesa.

While seating will be limited to accommodate social distancing, participants can attend remotely through a Zoom link that is posted on the meeting agenda.

Trustees are inviting a panel of speakers and members of the public to share input on returning students to campuses that suspended in-person instruction and transitioned to distance learning in mid-March.

In the meantime, the California Department of Public Health has issued interim guidance for schools, and representatives from OCDE and Orange County school districts have also released recommendations for reopening.

Locally elected school boards are expected to work with their superintendents, staff and families to approve and implement plans specific to each district.​

For more information on the forum, visit the Orange County Board of Education website.

column31: Dear Friends, There’s a lot of confusion out there concerning governor Newsom’s ability to continue to issue executive orders￼, in particular his new alleged state wide mask order￼. Democrats are suggesting that a federal appellate judge ￼removed limits on Newsom’s power to issue emergency orders during the pandemic, not true. Here is what actually happened and it is all very political... On June 12, 2020, Sutter Superior Court Judge Perry Parker granted the lawmakers' request for a temporary restraining order against a recent Newsom executive order that allowed counties to reduce precincts on Election Day if they provide in-person voting centers for at least three days prior. The GOP filing did not challenge the governor's original executive order mandating that all California voters receive mail ballots for the November election. The judge also sided with the two Republican lawmakers by more broadly requiring Newsom to refrain from new orders that might be interpreted as infringing on the Legislature’s law making responsibilities. Presiding Justice Vance Raye of the Third District Court of Appeal, in a two-sentence directive, stayed the lower court’s action and barred Perry from issuing any further orders, but he allowed court proceedings to continue. Judge Perry has set a June 26 hearing in the case. Judge Raye did not reverse the lower court’s finding. CA Assemblymen James Gallagher and Kevin Kiley said in a joint statement it is an “entirely ordinary temporary stay” and accusing the governor of “playing procedural games” by requesting the stay. Justice Raye did not “remove limits on Newsom’s power to issue emergency orders during the pandemic,” he merely stayed the Superior Courts blocking of Newsom’s order on ballots and issuing further orders that conflicted with existing state law. Justice Ray’s stay did not give Newsom any additional authority to issue orders outside of government code restrictions. A judge, a member of the judicial branch, does not have the power to make laws, or change the law, in particular here, the government code 8627.5 (b) which limits the duration of an emergency order declaration and any other orders issued by the governor pursuant to the alleged emergency to 60 days at most. The government code can only be changed by the California legislature. As I have stated, it is my firm legal opinion governor Newsom’s original declaration of emergency and any orders he has made pursuant to that declaration are invalid as a matter of law and do not meet US and California constitutional scrutiny. The coronavirus is real, it is undoubtedly a serious health concern, but here in California and San Diego County it has never been a pandemic within the government code requirements. Statistically, it has proved to be no more dangerous than the common flu, heart disease, or motor vehicle accidents, Yet we haven’t banned people from eating fatty foods, or driving their cars￼. Rather, Democrats across the nation have admittedly used it to harm the best economy in history and the hard-working citizens of this country, in particular small businesses. The fact that the coronavirus has affected the health of hundreds of thousands of Americans is terribly sad, the fact that it has been further used as a political weapon to wreck the economies of this country for attempted political power is despicable, it is attempted tyranny on top of an seeming accidental health tragedy, or maybe it was all intentional, which is criminal. 👎🏼 God bless San Diego, God bless the USA￼ 🙏🏻🇺🇸

column35: Mayor Kell Palguta
column36:
- Hey everyone, here’s an update on recent COVID-19 developments from Governor Doug Ducey. 
- As many of you have heard, the governor has asked mayors of Arizona cities and towns to decide if they will require their communities to wear masks. 
- The Town of Prescott Valley has made the decision to not require the community to wear masks at this time. 
- We understand the concerns from everyone in the community, people are scared and we don’t know what’s happening, and we get that. 
- I want everyone to understand how we came about our decision. 
- Yavapai County currently has an infection rate of 0.2%, which is 409 confirmed cases out of over 230,000 people. 
- Information regarding the 7 COVID-19 related deaths we’ve had has come in. All of these individuals are over 65 years old and a few were in their 80’s. Of those seven, a few have passed away in a location outside of Yavapai County. The reason they have been counted in Yavapai County is because their residential address is here. That’s why sometimes the numbers will change, the County Health Services is trying to determine where exactly these deaths need to be counted. 
- We also want to look at how would the enforcement of wearing masks take place. What if people weren’t wearing them correctly? What age were we going to make a minimum requirement to wear a mask? 
- With that in mind, along with the numbers, is how we came up with our decision.  
- We also recognize that the numbers will continue to rise, and people will continue to be infected. We also know that deaths will continue to rise. 
- Currently there are some hospitalizations from people who were in nursing homes, above the age of 80, and they have other underlying issues as well as COVID-19. 
- We understand that the risk is going to be present here in Yavapai County over the few weeks, people will come up for festivities that we have. Keep in mind, everything that we do going forward, we are encouraging social distancing. 
- We are encouraging you to wear a mask if you are comfortable doing so. 
- If you are not comfortable going out and attending events, I encourage you to stay home. You do not have to have contact with anyone if you are feeling uneasy at this time, and that is okay. 
- We are going to move forward in a direction that is positive for this community and we are monitoring the progress of this with the Yavapai County Health Services every single day. 
- Your health and the best for Prescott Valley is in mind.
- We encourage personal responsibility for how you do things. We want you to make your own decisions moving forward on what you feel comfortable with. You make that decision for you and your family; I don’t want to be there person telling you what you can and can’t do. 
- Everyone, we will get through this and I will see you next time. 

For more info on COVID-19 in Yavapai County, visit: www.yavapai.us/chs

For more info on COVID-19 in Arizona, visit: www.azdhs.gov

For more info on Governor Ducey's Executive Order, visit: www.azgovernor.gov

column35: Mayor Kell Palguta
column36:
Governor Ducey announced today that he will leave the decision to make masks required in public up to each Mayor to decide.  I appreciate the Governor recognizing that all communities are different and should not be treated the same.

The Town of Prescott Valley will NOT currently be requiring masks when out in public.  I have made this decision based off of the current infection rate, how our Town has been responding to this Covid-19 issue as well as to the logistical challenges that enforcement would pose on our first responders. 

I am asking the following of our citizens to consider:

#1 Continue to practice and respect safe distancing practices when at all possible in public

#2 If you do not feel comfortable or are at risk  being in public around individuals not wearing masks then YOU should make the risk vs reward decision to stay home or not. 

#3 Every citizen's  overall health in our community is top priority to me but so is the right to each citizen to make independent decisions on what is the best for them and their family.

#4 Nothing is stopping someone who is concerned of contracting Covid 19 from staying at home, ordering food from the grocer to be delivered to their home and self isolating themselves from others until this threat is over.

column31: We can’t very well argue with these “ authoritative sources” now can we? Please regard the language used in this WHO document in the excerpt below regarding the use of masks and hand washing : “experimental”, “ insufficient scientific evidence from RCT’s”, “ lack of efficacy” , “ lack of evidence for effectiveness” As per the WHO: “Experimental studies suggest that hand hygiene can reduce virus on the hands. However, there is insufficient scientific evidence from RCTs to support the efficacy of hand hygiene alone to reduce influenza transmission in influenza epidemics and pandemics. Hand hygiene is an important intervention to reduce the risk of other common infectious diseases; therefore, it should be recommended at all times, regardless of the lack of efficacy against confirmed influenza reported in a number of RCTs. There is also a lack of evidence for the effectiveness of improved respiratory etiquette and the use of face masks in community settings during influenza epidemics and pandemics. Nevertheless, these NPIs may be conditionally recommended for ill persons because of other considerations (e.g. the high cost of face masks), and they are generally feasible and acceptable. It is likely that these personal interventions could be effective if implemented in combination.” https://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/handle/10665/329438/9789241516839-eng.pdf?ua=1

column31: Please regard the language used in this WHO document in the excerpt below regarding the use of masks and hand washing : “experimental”, “ insufficient scientific evidence from RCT’s”, “ lack of efficacy” , “ lack of evidence for effectiveness” As per the WHO: “Experimental studies suggest that hand hygiene can reduce virus on the hands. However, there is insufficient scientific evidence from RCTs to support the efficacy of hand hygiene alone to reduce influenza transmission in influenza epidemics and pandemics. Hand hygiene is an important intervention to reduce the risk of other common infectious diseases; therefore, it should be recommended at all times, regardless of the lack of efficacy against confirmed influenza reported in a number of RCTs. There is also a lack of evidence for the effectiveness of improved respiratory etiquette and the use of face masks in community settings during influenza epidemics and pandemics. Nevertheless, these NPIs may be conditionally recommended for ill persons because of other considerations (e.g. the high cost of face masks), and they are generally feasible and acceptable. It is likely that these personal interventions could be effective if implemented in combination.” https://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/handle/10665/329438/9789241516839-eng.pdf?ua=1

column36:
== Vaccine Adjuvants Cause Autoimmunity ==
Adjuvants are used in vaccines to activate the immune system. They are toxicants (i.e. poisons) included in the vaccine against which the body attempts to protect itself. During this heightened immune response, the body also creates antibodies against the vaccine antigen (the dead or attenuated virus, for example) that it would normally ignore.

But these adjuvants create a series of non-specific effects or NSEs; the specific effect is the creation of antibodies against the antigen. A more colloquial term for NSEs is "side-effects."

One primary NSE is the creation of antibodies **against the vaccine recipient's own human tissue**. In other words, the body starts to attack itself. The US currently has approximately 50 million people experiencing autoimmune reactions and autoimmunity is especially prevalent in women [1]. The US population is also one of the most vaccinated populations on the planet.

This just-published paper discusses one of "immunology's dirty little secrets," that including a poison is required for many vaccines to work [2] (btw, there are other secrets [3]).

Amazingly, doctors and public health officials deny that one of the primary NSEs of vaccines is an autoimmune reaction. Moreover, they have no official reason for the autoimmune epidemic—but vaccines, they say, have nothing to do with it.

Those following the science know that this is false. Every vaccine increases the chance of the body attacking itself such that "polyautoimmunity" is now common. If one is experiencing autoimmunity, it is actually more likely to have *multiple* autoimmune conditions than just one. That's how bad the autoimmune epidemic has become.

This case study discusses a 34-year-old researcher who mistakenly injected himself with Freund's adjuvant and experienced multiple autoimmune reactions: arthritis [4], serositis [5], and epididymitis [6]. Note that arthritis is listed on some vaccine product inserts as a risk of the injection.

The syndrome for this is called ASIA—autoimmune/inflammatory syndrome induced by adjuvants. 

In my view, it is not a question of whether vaccine adjuvants are contributing to the autoimmune epidemic; it's merely a matter of quantifying how much is its contribution, which is difficult to do because public health authorities deny that vaccines can cause these issues so as not to scare the population and thus risk vaccination rates declining. 

"Yes, with these vaccines your child will not get a self-clearing temporary infection of the measles but may get multiple autoimmune reactions that may cause extensive suffering and early death" is a conversation they don't want to have with parents. Thus, those medical professionals who know about ASIA lie and deny it. Many other medical professionals are poorly trained and thus don't even know vaccines are a major contributor to the autoimmunity epidemic.

Immunologist's Little Dirty Secret Finger: A Case Report of Polyautoimmunity Following an Accidental Self-injection of Complete Freund's Adjuvant

People of all ages, sexes and races can and do have arthritis, and it is the leading cause of disability in America. More than 50 million adults and 300,000 children have some type of arthritis. It is most common among women and occurs more frequently as people get older."

https://www.arthritis.org/health-wellness/about-arthritis/understanding-arthritis/what-is-arthritis

Between the two layers, there’s a thin film of serous fluid that allows your organs to move smoothly within your body. For example, your lungs can expand when you take a deep breath without being damaged by friction.

Serositis occurs when your serous membranes are inflamed. This makes it hard for your organs to smoothly slide around in your body, causing pain and other symptoms."

This is the data I have been waiting for!! 

"But the pandemic experience has brought on a surprising effect on this expected death rate among children. Starting in early March, expected deaths began a sharp decline, from an expected level of around 700 deaths per week to well under 500 by mid‐April and throughout May.(1) As untimely deaths spiked among the elderly in Manhattan nursing homes and in similar settings all over the country, something mysterious was saving the lives of children. As springtime in America came along with massive disruptions in family life amid near universal lockdowns, roughly 30% fewer children died."

Not only does this paper lay out some of the covid data in regards to all cause deaths and differences in death rates from states with variation in state lockdown status, but the biggest news yet - the decrease in child deaths is almost completely due to the decrease in infant deaths.  They go on to link the decrease in vaccine orders and routine vaccination visits ("well visits") with this decrease in infant death.  

They are drawing initial conclusions and connections supporting what many of us have been saying all along - vaccines cause SIDS - and at alarming numbers.  How many infants have been saved from SIDS due to the lockdown?

See some of the charts below, and here is the link to the paper https://www.cohealthchoice.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Lessons-from-the-Lockdown-vF-6-17-20.pdf

column34: During sports, a concussion can happen as the result of a blow or hit to the head. Symptoms typically present within the first seven to 10 days after an individual hits their head.
column35: Southwest Brain Performance Centers
column36:
A concussion is a mild Traumatic Brain Injury (mTBI) that occurs after a blow to the head. Symptoms of a concussion typically present within the first seven to 10 days after an individual hits their head, and can resolve within three months. However, if left untreated, they can persist for a year or more. Post-Concussion Syndrome (PCS) is a complex condition in which various symptoms last for several weeks to even months after the initial concussion. 

Want to schedule a 20 minute complimentary phone consultation to learn more? Visit our website!

column31: Why? Why? That was the question resounding in my mind. I was 12, learning about the French Revolution. Why did it go so wrong? Amazing visions of what should be. Liberté. Egalité. Fraternité. And then more and more heads got chopped off. How could that be? Then there was the Russian Revolution. It was the same thing. Only worse. No one had answers. The question stayed with me, tugging at me. I still had high hopes for other revolutions, like the one in Cambodia. Soon, 2 million dead. The Killing Fields. I learned to have misgivings any time I heard about a revolution. Other people heralded the Arab Spring. Not me. I kept digging away at why things kept going wrong, got a PhD (Psychology, Sociology and Cultural Studies). I found a few answers. Human vulnerabilities, like fear, rage, hatred, greed, desire for power, self-righteousness, and group delusion. A lack of checks and balances – perfect for dictatorships. Please read & share. FROM: Derek Sloan: Conservative. No Apology. Kim, Last Wednesday, Erin O’Toole released his official policy platform. Originally, his section on climate policy contained the promise that he would “[end] fossil fuel subsidies, a form of corporate welfare.” Even Peter MacKay, of all people, noticed and remarked that this was a phrase that didn’t sound like it was written by a Conservative, and, by Thursday, O’Toole back peddled and removed the offending phrase. O’Toole replaced it with some vague language about simplifying the tax code to help the resource sector. But the flag was raised, and what a bright Red Tory flag it is. Yes, O’Toole’s platform also promises to end Trudeau’s carbon tax, but Erin still calls for the implementation of a national carbon mechanism for large industrial emitters, which would be paid for by the industry rather than by ordinary Canadians. Erin O’Toole knows very well that companies pass on costs to consumers, the ordinary Canadians. In other words, O’Toole’s plan is to scrap Trudeau’s carbon tax and replace it with an “O’Toole” carbon tax, and you will still pay for it. I applaud Peter MacKay for taking O’Toole to task for his deceptive carbon tax policy, but MacKay’s own position on the matter makes no more sense than does O’Toole’s. MacKay is promising to scrap the carbon tax, but at the same time still “try” to meet the emissions goals of the Paris Agreement, which he calls “aspirational”. I have a word for MacKay’s proposal: impossible! Even having the Paris emissions goals as “aspirational” gives the environmentalist left a “green light” to pursue a host of policies that are aimed at destroying the Canadian energy industry. We won’t ever reach the Paris targets, but a few more Trudeau-style governments and we might just see the end of one of our most important industries. And what about Leslyn Lewis? Lewis has, these past few months, been critical of the carbon tax and of Canada’s obligations under the Paris Agreement, but she has never definitively promised to take Canada out of the accord. Day by day, we are learning more about Dr. Lewis’ actual green agenda. A recently unearthed tweet from February, 2019, might shed some light on the subject: Sustainable Development Goals and Paris Convention is an essential part of any international law practice. Glad to see your initiative at the UN! In her enthusiastic applause for Peter MacKay’s environmental law practice, it seems as though Leslyn Lewis spoke much more favourably of things like the Paris Agreement (she calls it the Paris Convention) than she has been these past few weeks. Where does Leslyn Lewis really stand on the Paris Agreement? The carbon tax? Ontario’s Green Energy Act? Do her positions of 2019 conflict with her positions of 2020? Red Tory policies—and their new, improved “Green Tory” version—will cost ordinary Canadians their livelihoods and Canada its autonomy. We can’t afford the Red-Green Tory agenda, just like we can’t afford more Justin Trudeau. I am the only candidate who remains dedicated to repealing Trudeau’s unconstitutional carbon tax grab. And now there should be no doubt that I am the ONLY candidate committed to taking Canada out of the Paris Agreement, which sets unrealistic emissions targets that only lead to the hamstringing of Canada’s economy in trying to comply with them. Sincerely, Derek Sloan's signature Derek Sloan Member of Parliament https://www.dereksloan.ca PS: I’m running for CPC leader to put Canadians first, ahead of all international bodies and global interests that don’t care about Canadians. column31: So while it is a while away, I am going to pitch out an idea I have to see what all of your thoughts are! Every year, I drive across Canada for Christmas time. Knowing how there are programs in larger cities that provide small bursaries or toys for kids for families who can’t afford it for Christmas, I can’t help but think of the small towns across Canada who can’t get traction or funding for programs like that. My idea is to start a fundraiser for that exact purpose. My goal would be to raise money to get gift cards for families so that they can get toys for their children in their community and support local businesses at the same time. I am hoping on providing $50 per child per family that this fundraiser can support, seeing as I normally leave a few weeks before Christmas. I can contact small community newspapers across Canada along Highway 1 or 16 to advertise this program, identifying families that could use the help, and the amount of families helped would only be limited to as much as I can raise. I believe this would help make the Christmas season a little better for communities from Alberta to Ontario, and I would make it an annual program! So the question is, what are your thoughts on this idea, and if it kicks off, would any of you be willing to join me in this?

column35: Steven
column36:
For a small amount of perspective at this moment, imagine you were born in 1900. When you are 14, World War I starts, and ends on your 18th birthday with 22 million people killed. Later in the year, a Spanish Flu epidemic hits the planet and runs until you are 20. Fifty million people die from it in those two years. Yes, 50 million.

When you're 29, the Great Depression begins. Unemployment hits 25%, global GDP drops 27%. That runs until you are 33. The country nearly collapses along with the world economy. When you turn 39, World War II starts. You aren’t even over the hill yet.

When you're 41, the United States is fully pulled into WWII. Between your 39th and 45th birthday, 75 million people perish in the war and the Holocaust kills six million. At 52, the Korean War starts and five million perish.

At 64 the Vietnam War begins, and it doesn’t end for many years. Four million people die in that conflict. Approaching your 62nd birthday you have the Cuban Missile Crisis, a tipping point in the Cold War. Life on our planet, as we know it, could well have ended. Great leaders prevented that from happening.

As you turn 75, the Vietnam War finally ends. Think of everyone on the planet born in 1900. How do you survive all of that? A kid in 1985 didn’t think their 85 year old grandparent understood how hard school was. Yet those grandparents (and now great grandparents) survived through everything listed above.

Perspective is an amazing art. Let’s try and keep things in perspective. Let’s be smart, help each other out, and we will get through all of this. In the history of the world, there has never been a storm that lasted. This too, shall pass.

*Share this with the world!*

You can hear about it here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0UN5kqiIzxs&feature=youtube I was feeling discouraged this evening. So much insanity around me. A 6-time convicted criminal, drugs in his system, passing a counterfeit bill, is being widely hailed as a hero. For what? For being a black person wrongfully killed by a white police officer. That does not make anyone a hero. A retired black police officer was killed trying to stop black looters. That man qualifies as a hero. But he is not being hailed as a hero. Anyway, I was feeling discouraged. Norman's story encouraged me. He is not giving up. If he can go on, so can we. Do you have heroes or heroines? Who inspires you?
